<HR>

<DL>
<DT><B>Why are there two waste disposal systems? </B>
<DD>When the 1985 Solid Waste Management Plan was established
Vancouver already had an existing system - the Vancouver system
was rolled into the GVRD system but maintained the same ownership.
<DT><B>Where can I get education materials, particularly posters
which promote the 3Rs? </B>
<DD>Please contact the Communications and Education Department
of the GVRD at (604) 432-6339.
<DT><B>Where can I find information on plastic recycling? </B>
<DD>Please contact the Recycling Hotline at (604) 732-9253 or
toll free 1-800-667-4321.
<DT><B>How do I begin composting? </B>
<DD>Check out the composting information on this site at <A HREF="/waste/bro/swcomp1.html">http://www.gvrd.bc.ca/waste/bro/swcomp1.html</A>

<DT><B>Why doesn't (or when will) my apartment have recycling
service? </B>
<DD>Each municipality differs - please contact your municipality.
The phone numbers are listed in the blue pages of the BC Tel Directory.
<DT><B>How much (paper/organics/plastic/etc.) is in our garbage?
</B>
<DD>'Garbage' from Homes and Businesses, (does not include large-scale
demolition, landclearing and construction wastes)
</DL>
