<HEAD>

<TITLE>Parks FAQ</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Tom Berryhill">
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor=#FFFFFF text=#000000>

<CENTER><A HREF="/index.html"><IMG SRC="/go/medarch/home/head6.gif" BORDER=0></A>

</CENTER>

<H1>Regional Parks FAQ</H1>
<P>

<FONT SIZE=+2>(F</FONT>requently <FONT SIZE=+2>A</FONT>sked <FONT SIZE=+2>Q</FONT>uestions<FONT SIZE=+2>)</FONT>


<DL>
<DT><B>Q. Is Stanley Park a regional park?</B> 
<DD>A. No, Stanley Park is operated by the City of Vancouver.
For information call (604) 257-8400.
<DT><B>Q. What is the difference between provincial and regional
parks?</B> 
<DD>A. Both regional parks and provincial parks are large natural
areas that provide many outdoor recreation opportunities. Regional
parks are the largest parks that can be found in the urban areas,
and normally are visited by people from within the urban area.
There are 25 regional parks within sixty miles of downtown Vancouver;
they are located closer to the cities and towns that make up the
Lower Mainland. By contrast there are only seven provincial parks
within this same area. Provincial parks often protect natural
areas that are unique in the entire province, while regional parks
protect the landscapes that make up this particular part of the
province. For information on provincial parks call (604) 924-2200.
For information on regional parks call (604)432-6350.
<DT><B>Q. Where can I camp in regional parks?</B> 
<DD>A. You can camp along the Fraser River in Derby Reach Regional
Park, Langley Township, or at Matsqui Trail Regional Park, Abbotsford,
between March 1 and November 30. All campers must register and
pay a fee. For more information call GVRD East Area Parks office
at (604) 530-4983.
<DT><B>Q. How do I rent Minnekhada Lodge?</B> 
<DD>A. Call GVRD Parks' Bookings and Facilities office at (604)
432-6352 (between 9 a.m. and 3:30 p.m., Monday to Friday) for
rental information on Minnekhada Lodge (Minnekhada Regional Park,
Coquitlam) and many other facilities. We can also mail you a brochure
featuring information on all of our reservable facilities.
<DT><B>Q. Where do I find information on special events and interpretive
programs?</B> 
<DD>A. Call GVRD Parks' program registration office at (604) 432-6359.
We will send you our current listing of activities and/or add
your name to our mailing list to receive a program brochure three
times a year.
<DT><B>Q. In which parks can I go mountain biking or cycling?</B>

<DD>A. You are welcome to ride your mountain bike in Pacific Spirit
Regional Park (near UBC) on designated trails. For other cycling
opportunities visit Iona Beach Regional Park (Richmond) or Matsqui
Trail Regional Park (Abbotsford).
<DT><B>Q. Which parks offer hiking trails?</B> 
<DD>A. Belcarra Regional Park (Port Moody, Belcarra), Minnekhada
Regional Park (Coquitlam), Kanaka Creek Regional Park (Maple Ridge),
Capilano River Regional Park (North/West Vancouver), Crippen Regional
Park (Bowen Island), and Pacific Spirit Regional Park (near UBC).
Detailed trail information is included in park maps, available
from park kiosks.
<DT><B>Q. Where can I find information on natural history in regional
parks?</B> 
<DD>A. Some information is in park brochures, available from park
kiosks. You are also welcome to contact our interpretive specialists;
please call GVRD Parks main office at (604) 432-6350 and your
call will be directed to the appropriate specialist. If you like,
bring your questions to our two visitor centres at Burnaby Lake
Regional Park (4519 Piper Avenue, Burnaby) and Campbell Valley
Regional Park (corner of 8th Ave. and 200th St., Langley), which
are open weekends from late May to the Labour Day weekend.
<DT><B>Q. What are your parks opening and closing hours?</B> 
<DD>A. Most parks are generally open from 8 a.m. to dusk.
<DT><B>Q. How do I get information on specific parks?</B>
 
<DD>A. <A HREF="/go/todo/pkloc.html"><B>Click here </B></A>to pick a specific park or call the following numbers, Monday to Friday:
<UL>
<LI>(604) 530-4983 (8 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.) for information on Aldergrove
Lake, Barnston Island, Campbell Valley, Derby Reach, Glen Valley,
Grant Narrows, Kanaka Creek, Matsqui Trail, Surrey Bend or Tynehead
Regional Parks.
<LI>(604) 520-6442 (8:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.) for information on
Belcarra, Boundary Bay, Burnaby Lake, Colony Farm, Deas Island,
Minnekhada, or Widgeon Marsh Regional Parks.
<LI>(604) 224-5739 (8 a.m. to 4 p.m.) for information on Capilano
River, Crippen, Iona Beach, Lynn Headwaters, or Pacific Spirit
Regional Parks.
</UL>
</DL>
<P>

