<HEAD>
<TITLE>Creating Our Future: the CD-ROM
</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor=#FFFFFF text=#000000 link=#007050 vlink=#090090><A NAME="TOP"></A>
<CENTER><A HREF="/index.html"><IMG SRC="/go/medarch/home/head6.gif" BORDER=0></A>
</CENTER>
<H1>Creating Our Future: the CD-ROM
</H1>
<P>The CD-ROM, <CITE>Creating Our Future,</CITE> contains three interactive computer simulations 
to help the players learn more about choices they can make to improve the environment in the next 
30 years. You can purchase the CD-ROM at <A HREF="http://www.scienceworld.bc.ca">Science World</A>, 
or <A HREF="http://www.scienceworld.bc.ca/TOYS.HTML">order it from their gift shop</A>.
<HR width=60% align=left>
<IMG SRC="../av_media/aliceliv.gif" align=right HSPACE=5 VSPACE=5 
alt="Picture of a teen-aged girl">Help! Alice has been digitized right into a computer simulation of 
the environment in the Greater Vancouver Region, thirty years from now, in the 2020's. 
It was a strange experience for her, and a little disorienting... like stepping through the
"looking glass!"  Things are a little backwards. She thinks she actually belongs in the future
and is trapped here in our present. She wants to get home to the future, but the only way she 
can get out of the simulation is to find a way to improve the environment. Ironically, if and when she
does get out, it may indeed be the future.</P>
<P>
What kind of future will it be, though?  The one that the programmers created in the simulation
is not very nice. There is so much smog and garbage, and not enough
water, that she decided to do something about it. She has found a way to use the viewport on 
the simulator to talk to you; but only when the programmers are not around.  Additionally, she
has figured out a way for <b>you</b> to change the programmer's assumptions about human behaviour
and affect the simulation results for the future. If you do change the factors and improve the
environment, Alice can get home.  More on that later.
</P>
<P>Right now, you can use your <A HREF="/go/arch/software.html#quicktime">Quicktime player</A> to hear what 
Alice says about this. 
</P>
<P align=center>
<B>Will you find ways to improve the environment?</B></P>
<P align=center><font size=-2>(click for 563k movie)</font><BR>
<A HREF="../av_media/ifyoudo.mov"><IMG SRC="../av_media/aliceifu.gif" ALT="Picture of Alice"></A>
<BR clear=all><font size=-1>"Help me get out of here!"</font>
</P>
<HR width=50%>
<H2>The Environmental Simulator</H2>
<P>The simulator allows you to go through parts of a house and make decisions about things you 
find there. There is a floorplan map of the house so you can see where you are, and the viewport on 
the simulator flies you to wherever you want to go!
</P>
<P align=center><font size=-2>(click for 865k movie of instructions)</font><BR>
<A HREF="../av_media/imalice.mov"><IMG SRC="../av_media/simctl1.jpg"></A>
<BR clear=all><font size =-1>(Control Panel)</font>
</P>
<P>Alice's plan for you has one problem: the simulator might detect your presence and mistake your changes
for a computer virus! The longer you take and the more wrong choices you make, the more likely it is that
the <I>Virus Detector</I> will find you. Alice will warn you, if it is getting close, by flashing the light 
in the upper left corner of the control panel.
</P>
<HR>
<P>
</P>
<P align=left>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font size=-2>(click for 629k movie)</font><BR>
<A HREF="../av_media/flyin.mov"><IMG SRC="../av_media/flyin.gif" align=left></A>
<blockquote>
We did say that the simulator would fly you around the house, so to sample that action, let's take
a look at how we get into the house in the first place.
</blockquote>
<BR clear=all>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font size =-1>(Flight into the house)</font>
</P>
<HR>
<H2>Now it's up to you</H2>
<P>
</P>Once you are inside the house, Alice will give you advice on how you are doing and what to do next. 
But, finding your way through the house and making the choices is up to you. The simulator will help you
see what differences your choices are making... better for you, or better for the Earth. Sometimes you
can make choices that are "Win / Win" and are better for everyone.
</P>
<P>There are three different simulations:
<OL>
<LI>Air Quality & Transportation
<LI>Drinking Water & Wastewater
<LI>Waste Reduction and Recycling
</OL>
</P>
<P>Each has its own challenges. If you don't get it right the first time, Alice will advise you on what
to do differently on your next time around.  Each time you finish going through the house, you can run
the simulation to see how your changes (if adopted by others too) will affect the future, 30 years from now.
</P>
<P><IMG ALIGN=left SRC="../av_media/simulate.gif" HSPACE=10 ALT="Simulator results showing conditions are worse">
It's not always easy, but with time, you will learn how to make a positive affect on the future. Sometimes 
it is the smallest thing, that you usually take for granted, that will make the difference. Once you see the
difference in the simulator, can you also make those changes in your daily life? Try it! In thirty years, 
the "Alice's" of this world will actually be living with your decisions of today.
<P>
<BR clear=all>
<HR>
