<HEAD>

<TITLE>GREATER VANCOUVER KEY FACTS

</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor=#FFFFFF text=#000000>

<CENTER><A HREF="/index.html"><IMG SRC="/go/medarch/home/head6.gif" BORDER=0></A></CENTER>

<BR><A NAME="TOP">

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>GREATER VANCOUVER KEY FACTS</H1>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>A Statistical Profile of Greater Vancouver, Canada</H2>

<HR>

<P><I>Greater Vancouver Key Facts</I> has been prepared to provide a 

comprehensive statistical picture of Greater Vancouver. 

Key Facts is published annually in the summer.  It is available both 

<A HREF="#download"><B>electronically</B></A> and in 

<A HREF="#ordering"><B>paper</B></A> form.  You may want to look at its <A HREF="kftoc.html">

<B>Table of Contents</B></A> before downloading it.

</P>

<H2>THE GREATER VANCOUVER METROPOLITAN AREA</H2>



<P>

The Greater Vancouver region is located at the southwest corner

of the British Columbia mainland.  The Greater Vancouver Regional

District occupies 2,930 square kilometres at the mouth of the

Fraser River.

<P>

Greater Vancouver's setting, combined with its situation as the

key coastal port for Western Canada and its history, results in

an interesting mix of large and small communities.

<P>

The metropolitan community is centered on the City of Vancouver

on the Burrard Peninsula.  The adjoining municipalities to the

east, Burnaby, New Westminster, Coquitlam, Port Coquitlam, and

Port Moody share the Burrard Peninsula.  West Vancouver, Lions

Bay, North Vancouver City and District, Belcarra and Anmore are

located on the south slope of the Coastal Mountain range separated

from the peninsular communities by Burrard Inlet.  South of the

peninsula are the municipalities of Richmond, Delta, Surrey, White

Rock, Langley City and Township.  Maple Ridge and Pitt Meadows,

located to the north, joined the Greater Vancouver Regional Distict

(GVRD) in July 1995.  These communities are separated from the

peninsula by the Fraser River.

<P>

Together, these twenty municipalities make up both the Greater

Vancouver Regional District (GVRD) and Census Metropolitan Area

(CMA). A CMA is a large urbanized core together with adjacent

urban and rural areas which have a high degree of economic and

social integration.

</P>

<A NAME="ordering"></A>

<H2>Ordering a Paper Copy of Greater Vancouver Key Facts</H2>

<P><I>Key Facts</I> is published annually in the summer and is about 130 pages.  To order 

a paper copy of the document, please contact the GVRD Communications

and Education department:</P>

<BLOCKQUOTE>

<B>GVRD Communications and Education</B><BR>

3rd Floor, 4330 Kingsway<BR>

Burnaby BC  V5H 4G8<BR>

Phone: (604) 432-6339<BR>

Fax: (604) 432-6399

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<P>or by email to: <A HREF="mailto:webmaster@gvrd.bc.ca">webmaster@gvrd.bc.ca</A>

</P>

<A NAME="download"></A>

<H2>Downloading a Copy of Greater Vancouver Key Facts</H2>

<P>The electronic copy of <I>Key Facts</I> is in both Adobe&#153; Acrobat&#153; and 

Microsoft&#174; Word&#153; format. </P>

<DL><DT><IMG SRC="../medarch/arch/PDFmid.gif"> Adobe Acrobat version

<DD>The Acrobat format version can be viewed with the 

<A HREF="software.html#acrobat">Acrobat Reader software</A>. 

It will allow you to read, print and copy selected text.  If you would like

to manipulate the data, sort it, or make graphs from it, you will need to get 

the Microsoft Word version.

<DT><IMG SRC="../medarch/arch/wordicon.gif"> Microsoft Word version

<DD>The Word version contains embedded Excel spreadsheets which can be 

manipulated with Microsoft Excel by double clicking on the spreadsheet of

interest while in Word. If you do not have Microsoft Word, and are using

Microsoft Windows, you can view Word documents with the 

<A HREF="software.html#word">

Microsoft Word Viewer</A>. The Word version is provided in formats compressed

for Apple Macintosh&#174; and PC users.

</DL>

<DL><DT>Download:

<DD>&nbsp;<A HREF="../../archive/planning/reports/keyfacts.pdf"><IMG SRC="../medarch/arch/PDFmid.gif" 

BORDER=0> <B>Adobe Acrobat</B> version of <I>GVRD Key Facts</I></A> [1.2 MB]



<DD><IMG SRC="../medarch/arch/wordicon.gif"> <B>Microsoft Word</B> versions:

<DD><UL>



<LI><A HREF="../../archive/planning/reports/keyfacts.sit"> Macintosh / PC version of <I>GVRD Key Facts</I></A> (use <A HREF="software.html#stuffit">StuffIt Expander</A>) [1.8 MB] 

<LI><A HREF="../../archive/planning/reports/keyfacts.zip"> PC version of <I>GVRD Key Facts</I></A> (use <A HREF="software.html#winzip">WinZip</A>) [1.6 MB]

<LI><A HREF="../../archive/planning/reports/keyfacts.exe"> Self-extracting PC version of <I>GVRD Key Facts</I></A> (keyfacts.exe) [1.6 MB]

</UL>

</DL>

