<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Strategic Planning Department</TITLE></HEAD><body bgcolor=#FFFFFF text=#000000><CENTER><A HREF="../../index.html"><IMG SRC="../../go/medarch/home/head6.gif" BORDER=0></A></CENTER><H1>Strategic Planning Department</H1><H3>Phone: (604) 432-6375</H3><P>Growth and development are inevitble in the region, but the consequences neednot be undesirable or unintended. Strategic Planning, working with municipalities, residentsand other governments, develops plans to manage growth in ways that are cost-effectiveand enhance the region's livability. The department also provides some municipalservices to the two electoral areas.<P>The Strategic Planning department works in close co-operation with municipal planningdepartments. These include research on regional development trends, activities to <AHREF="sppers1.html">improve the region's economy</A> and development of a region-widetransportation plan. The department compiles and shares current dataand  forecasts on land use, population, the economy, employment and transportation withmunicipalities, the private sector and other agencies. <P>The Strategic Planning department is now weaving the values and goals of Creating Our Futureinto the <A HREF="../futur.html">Livable Region Strategic Plan</A>, a blueprint on how the region's communities and residents can manage growth andmaintain Greater Vancouver's livability. The strategic plan provides a regional framework forGVRD programs and municipal community plans, guidelines for projects by the provincial andfederal governments as well as the private sector, and a reference point for individualaction. <P><HR><P><A HREF="../../index.html"><IMG SRC="../../go/medarch/home/smhome.gif" HSPACE=15 BORDER=0></A><A HREF="../../go/dept/depts.html#gvrd"><IMG SRC="../../go/medarch/home/gvrdsm.gif" HSPACE=2 BORDER=0></A><BR>[<A HREF="../../index.html">GVRD Home</A>] [<A HREF="../../go/dept/depts.html#gvrd">GVRD Departments</A>][<A HREF="../../go/work/futur.html">Livable Region Strategic Plan</A>][<A HREF="sppers1.html">Economic Development Opportunities</A>][<A HREF="spind.html">Economic Indicators</A>]<BR><ADDRESS>For further information or feedback, please email us at <A HREF="mailto:webmaster@gvrd.bc.ca">webmaster@gvrd.bc.ca</A></ADDRESS></BODY><!-- Revised by: Kim, Feb 29, 1996-->   </BODY></HTML> 
