<H1>Air Quality</H1>
<P>Air is one of the most basic requirements for life. 
Without clean air, most living things cannot survive. 
And yet it's probably the natural resource we most take for granted. 
Clean air is colourless and odourless. It doesn't cost anything (yet) 
and there seems to be an abundant supply. We tend to ignore the 
presence of clean air. We only notice it when it's missing.
The documents below will give you more detail on the air quality of 
the greater Vancouver region.
<P>

<IMG  SRC="../medarch/air/lgair.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT HSPACE=25
VSPACE=20> 
<UL>
<H2><A NAME="menu">Ambient Air Quality Annual Report</A></H2>
