Water							  48.7 millionOther (includes parks, air quality, 9-1-1,strategic planning, labour relations, communications and education, general administration)					  33.7 million						Total	$319.8 million</PRE><HR>[<A HREF="#top">Top of the page</A>][<A HREF="#col">Next</A>]<PRE></PRE> <H3><A NAME="col">How Funds are Collected</A></H3><P> The GVRD obtains 77 per cent of its funds from the municipalities it serves, billing them for services provided. The cost of most services is apportioned on a property assessment basis. The funds are collected by the municipalities in muncipal tax bills and remitted to the GVRD. Allocations for hospitals and Regional District (parks, air quality control, 9-1-1 etc.) are specifically listed on the municipal tax notice. GVRD costs for other services, like water and sewer, are included in your municipal levy. The GVRD itself does not have direct taxing authority.<P>GVRD services this year will take about 14 per cent of your municipal tax bill.<HR>[<A HREF="#top">Top of the page</A>][<A HREF="#ave">Next</A>]<PRE></PRE>  <H3><A NAME="ave">1995 Regional Taxes on the Average Single Family Home</A> </H3> <P> <PRE>Municipality	 Regional  Sewers    Solid Waste   Water   Hospitals    Total 		 Dist.*		     & RecyclingAnmore		 170.90	   -		-	  -	    59.93	230.83Belcarra	 180.69	   -		-	  -	    60.22	240.91Burnaby		  34.53	   104.63	 74.04	   57.05    58.61	328.86Coquitlam	  36.17	   116.32	 93.49	   53.86    61.69	361.53Delta		  34.62	   103.85	  4.32	   97.63    58.84	299.26Langley City	  36.66	   115.00	  1.73	  143.88    62.61	359.88Langley Township  36.49     50.43	 74.50	   22.67    62.44	246.53Lions Bay	  32.43	   -		-	  -	    59.24	 91.67Maple Ridge	  25.11	   160.93	 75.48	   77.39   -		338.91New Westminster	  34.50	   119.98	 78.17	   97.49    58.61	388.75North Van. City	  34.10	    98.76	 79.84	   62.38    58.23	333.31North Van. Dist.  34.16	 