<HEAD> <TITLE>GVRD Board of Directors </TITLE>

</HEAD><body bgcolor=#FFFFFF text=#000000>
<CENTER><A HREF="../../index.html"><IMG SRC="../../go/
medarch/home/head6.gif" BORDER=0></A></CENTER>

<H1>GVRD Board of Directors 1996</H1> 

<P>

The GVRD's Board of Directors comprises elected representatives from the 22
communities in the metropolitan area.
<P>
Directors representing municipalities are appointed from their local council,
for a one-year term. In most cases the appointee is the Mayor. In the electoral
areas, which are unicorporated and do not have councils, regional Directors are
elected by the voters of the respective areas, to three-year terms.
<P>
Each municipality has one Board vote for every 20,000 of population. The most
recent Canada Census statistics are used in determining population figures. No
Director may hold more than five votes, with the result that the largest
municipalities in population - Vancouver, Surrey, Burnaby and Richmond - have
more than one Director.
<P>
The 1995 Board has 30 Directors with a total of 92 votes.
<P>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG SRC="../av_media/board.gif"></P ALIGN=CENTER>
