<!doctype html public \"-//W30//DTD W3 HTML 2.0//EN\"><!--Updated: November 21, 1995  by P.Moscovich--><HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Capilano Watershed</TITLE></HEAD><body bgcolor=#FFFFFF text=#000000><CENTER><A HREF=../../index.html><IMG SRC="../../go/medarch/home/head6.gif" BORDER=0></A></CENTER><CENTER><H1><A NAME="cap">Capilano Watershed</H1></CENTER><CENTER><A HREF="watsey.html">Seymour Watershed</A></CENTER><CENTER><A HREF="watcoq.html">Coquitlam Watershed</A></CENTER><P><CENTER><IMG ALIGN=center SRC="../av_media/capdam.gif"></CENTER></P><P><H1>Facts & Figures</H1><P><UL><LI><B>Provides approximately</B> 40% of total GVRD water supply  <HR><LI><B>Total land area:</B> 20,000 hectares <HR><LI><B>Size of main reservoir:</B> 312 hectares   <HR><LI><B>Depth of main reservoir:</B> 75 m   <HR><LI><B>Quantity of water in main reservoir when full:</B> 34 billion litres  <HR><LI><B>Highest annual rainfall recorded:</B> 4.5 m <HR></UL> <P><B>The Capilano Watershed</B> is the westernmost watershed in the region, forming part of the mountain range of the North Shore. This watershed area is very close to the ocean and parts of it receive the most rainfall each year.</P><P>Because of this heavy rainfall and its steep mountain slopes, Capilano characteristically has frequent periods of cloudy water. This is largely due to the fact that this watershed has glacial clay deposits throughout its lands, and the main reservoir is located within the largest of these deposits. Palisade Lake is an important alpine lake. Located in bedrock, this small but deep lake provides important secondary water storage.</P><HR><P><A HREF="../../index.html"><IMG SRC="../../go/medarch/home/smhome.gif" HSPACE=15 BORDER=0></A><A HREF="../../go/work/work.html"><IMG SRC="../../go/medarch/work/worksm.gif" HSPACE=2 BORDER=0></A><A HREF="../../go/work/water.html#menu"><IMG SRC="../../go/medarch/water/rdwat.gif" HSPACE=25 BORDER=0></A><BR>[<A HREF="../../index.html">GVRD Home</A>][<A HREF="../../go/work/work.html">Working with You</A>][<A HREF="../../go/work/water.html#menu">Water System</A>][<A HREF="watfact.html#menu">Water Facts</A>]<BR><ADDRESS>For further information or feedback, please email us at <A HREF="mailto:webmaster@gvrd.bc.ca">webmaster@gvrd.bc.ca</A></ADDRESS></BODY><!-- Modified by: A.Bains September 22 1995 -->  <!-- end include --> </HTML>
