<!doctype html public \"-//W30//DTD W3 HTML 2.0//EN\"><!-- Updated: November 21, 1995  by P. Moscovich--><HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Seymour Watershed</TITLE></HEAD><body bgcolor=#FFFFFF text=#000000><CENTER><A HREF=../../index.html><IMG SRC="../../go/medarch/home/head6.gif" BORDER=0></A></CENTER><CENTER><H1><A NAME="cap">Seymour Watershed</H1></CENTER><CENTER><A HREF="watcap.html">Capilano Watershed</A></CENTER><CENTER><A HREF="watcoq.html">Coquitlam Watershed</A></CENTER><H2>Facts & Figures</H2><UL> <LI><B>Provides approximately:</B> 40% of GVRD's total water supply  <HR> <LI><B>Total land area:</B> 18,000 hectares <HR> <LI><B>Size of main reservoir:</B> 262 hectares  <HR> <LI><B>Depth of main reservoir:</B> 19 m  <HR> <LI><B>Quantity of water in main reservoir when full:</B> 30 billion litres.  <HR> <LI><B>Highest annual rainfall recorded:</B> 4.3 m  <HR></UL><P><CENTER><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="../av_media/lake.gif"></CENTER></P><P><B>The Seymour Watershed</B> is found just to the east of the Capilano watershed, separated by a mountain ridge. It is also a typical coastal mountain area, and being close to the ocean, this area receives lots of rain and snow.</P> <P>The Seymour reservoir is the shallowest of all three main watershed reservoirs and has an extensive floodplain extending from the mouth of the Seymour River  into the watershed for about six kilometres. This flood plain consists of thick, easily eroded silt deposits that can cause cloudy water during heavy rain. However, the silt-sand sediment in the Seymour Watershed commonly settles to the bottom of the lake more quickly than the clay silt in the Capilano Watershed, because of its larger and heavier particle size.</P><P>The main Seymour reservoir is fed by Burwell and Loch Lomond alpine lakes.</P><HR><P><A HREF="../../index.html"><IMG SRC="../../go/medarch/home/smhome.gif" HSPACE=15 BORDER=0></A><A HREF="../../go/work/work.html"><IMG SRC="../../go/medarch/work/worksm.gif" HSPACE=2 BORDER=0></A><A HREF="../../go/work/water.html#menu"><IMG SRC="../../go/medarch/water/rdwat.gif" HSPACE=25 BORDER=0></A><BR>[<A HREF="../../index.html">GVRD Home</A>][<A HREF="../../go/work/work.html">Working with You</A>][<A HREF="../../go/work/water.html#menu">Water System</A>][<A HREF="watfact.html#menu">Water Facts</A>]<BR><ADDRESS>For further information or feedback, please email us at <A HREF="mailto:webmaster@gvrd.bc.ca">webmaster@gvrd.bc.ca</A></ADDRESS></BODY><!-- Modified by: A.Bains September 22 1995 -->  <!-- end include --> </HTML>
