<TITLE>Compost Demonstration Gardens
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<body bgcolor=#FFFFFF text=#000000>
<CENTER><A HREF="../../index.html"><IMG SRC="../../go/medarch/home/head6.gif" BORDER=0></A></CENTER>
<H1>Waste Reduction at Home</H1>
<H2>Composting</H2>
<H3>Compost Demonstration Gardens</H3>
<P>To help educate would-be compost enthusiasts, the Greater Vancouver Regional 
District and many of its member municipalities have created compost demonstration 
gardens that show visitors a number of different compost bins in action. Many of 
the gardens have people on hand to answer questions, and there are signs explaining 
the composting process. As well, a few of the gardens offer workshops or tours for 
school children, residents and community groups.
<P>This list was last updated: December 2,1996
