<!doctype html public \"-//W30//DTD W3 HTML 2.0//EN\"><!-- HTML Author:		Peter FralinCreated:	Thursday, August 10, 1995Revised: 	Thursday, August 10, 1995--><HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Township of Langley Compost Demonstration Garden</TITLE></HEAD><body bgcolor=#FFFFFF text=#000000><CENTER><A HREF="../../index.html"><IMG SRC="../../go/medarch/home/head6.gif" BORDER=0></A></CENTER><H1>Waste Reduction at Home</H1><H2>Composting</H2><H3>Township of Langley Compost Demonstration Garden</H3><P>The Langley Garden is the newest addition to the Compost Demonstration Gardens in the Greater Vancouver Regional District. In the spring of 1993, with financial support from the Township of Langley, Kwantlen College, and private and corporate sponsorship, including the B.C. Ministry of the Environment, the Greater Vancouver Regional District and the Environmental Partners Fund, to name only a few, construction of the garden began. The public participation in the official grand opening of the garden in August '93 gave organizers assurance that the garden would be utilized and supported by the residents of Langley. The garden is situated in a delightful nature setting in the Town Core.<P> <IMG SRC="../av_media/langley.gif" ALIGN=LEFT>In September 1993, financial contributions from the Township of Langley, the Royal Bank, and the Langley School Board were pooled to support two months of educational workshops for school children on worm composting. The response to this program has been very positive.<P>The garden contains nine backyard composters and five different worm bins. A canopy covers the outdoor teaching area. Adults can expect up-to-date information on their composting concerns. Children can learn the wonderful world of worms. Literature, wildflower seeds, and fresh vegetables and flower samples are available for visitors. The garden will serve as a focus for the future community outreach education programs.<HR>[<A HREF="../../index.html>GVRD Home</A>][<A HREF="../../go/work/work.html">Working with You</A>][<A HREF="../../go/work/solid.html#menu">Solid Waste</A>][<A HREF="../../waste/bro/swcomp1.html#menu">Composting</A>][<A HREF="../../waste/bro/swcomp2.html">Gardens List</A>]<BR><ADDRESS>For further information or feedback, please email us at <A HREF="mailto:webmaster@gvrd.bc.ca">webmaster@gvrd.bc.ca</A></ADDRESS></BODY></HTML>
