<HEAD>
<TITLE>Nutrifor
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<body bgcolor=#FFFFFF text=#000000>
<CENTER><A HREF="../../index.html"><IMG SRC="../../go/medarch/home/head6.gif" BORDER=0></A></CENTER>

<H1>Nutrifor&#153;</H1>

<P>
Every day the GVRD's five wastewater treatment plants produce about 200 tonnes of 
biosolids.
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../av_media/nutrifor.gif">
<P><FONT SIZE=-1>The longer needles in this image show plant growth after Nutrifor 
enhancement.</FONT></CENTER> 
<P>
Decades of research and development have proven that biosolids are
highly efficient slow-release soil conditioners and enhancers that add many valuable
nutrients such as nitrogen and phosphorus to the soil. The GVRD has registered its 
biosolids with the trademark Nutrifor, which is increasingly in demand to restore 
depleted soils in B.C. Over the past four years, the GVRD and a variety of partners 
have been demonstrating its environmental benefits on agricultural land, reclaimed 
mines, and landfills, highway margins, forests and even parkland.  
<P>
Nutrifor has made a dramatic difference. Trees at fertilized forest sites are healthy 
and grow faster, while plants and grass grow vigorously on sites treated with the GVRD's 
biosolids. 
<P>
Recycling biosolids just makes sense: returning organic matter and nutrients to the
earth. Successful commercial development of Nutrifor has the potential to become a
source of revenue for the GVRD, demonstrating the enduring value of the old adage, waste
not, want not.


