<title>El Ni&ntilde;o</title>
</head>
<body>
<div align=center>
<h1>El Ni&ntilde;o</h1>
</div>
<hr>
<em><strong>Image credit:</strong> 
December 1982 SST anomaly from the Reynold's blend analysis 
data provided by NCEP (NMC).  Image courtesy of James Scott 
and Andrew Loughe, NOAA/ERL/CDC.
</em>
<hr>
<ul>
<li><a href=/cdc/overview/background.shtml#nino>Research 
related to El Ni&ntilde;o</a>
<li><a href=/cdc/overview/background.shtml#enso>Research Results</a>
<li><a href="/~mcp/Cecile.forecast.html">Linear
Inverse Modeling prediction of ENSO SST</a>
</ul>
<hr>
<div align=center>
<em>
<a href=/cdc/overview/9596/diagnostic.html>Climate Processes</a> | 
<a href=/cdc/overview/extreme>Long Term Variations</a> | 
<a href=/cdc/overview/extreme>Short Term Extremes</a> | 
<a href=/~climsat/>Satellites</a> | 
<a href=/cdc/cdc_overview.html#data>Data Management</a>  </em>
</div>
