<head>
<TITLE>The GFDL-University Consortium</TITLE>
</head>
<body>
<center>
<img src="logo.gif" alt="">
<h2>The GFDL-University Consortium</h2>
</center>

<HR size=4>
The GFDL-University Consortium began in 1990 as 
a collaborative effort between the 
<a href="http://www.gfdl.gov/">Geophysical Fluid Dynamics Lab</a>
(GFDL), other <a href="http://www.noaa.gov/">NOAA</a> 
centers including the 
<a href="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/">Climate Diagnostics Center,</a> and 
several universities.  The purpose of the consortium is to design and 
analyze a series of general circulation model (GCM) simulations to 
increase the understanding of the maintenance of regional climates and 
the atmospheric response to sea surface temperature (SST) anomalies and 
other perturbations in the lower boundary. <p>
<blockquote>
<dl>
<dt><img alt = "o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/blueball.gif">
<a href="members.html">Consortium members</a>
<dd>

<dt><img alt = "o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/blueball.gif">
<a href="/~jds/gfdl_publications.html">Consortium publications</a>
<dd>
<ul>
<li><a href=gfdl.html>Introduction to the printed atlas</a>
</ul>
<dt><img alt = "o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/blueball.gif">
Model Descriptions:
<dd>
<ul>
<li><a href="r30.html">R30 Model</a>
</ul>

<dt><img alt = "o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/blueball.gif">
Experiments:
<dd>
<ul>
<li><a href="r15.experiments.html">R15 Experiments</a>
<li><a href="r30.experiments.html">R30 Experiments</a>
</ul>

<dt><img alt = "o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/blueball.gif">
<a href="/cgi-bin/DataMenus.pl?dataset=gfdl">
Access to the GFDL atlas</a>
<p>
<dd>
</dl>
</blockquote>
