<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>FNL plotting page</TITLE>
<!-- Changed by: Cathy Smith, 12-Jul-1996 -->
<meta name=Interactive plots of climate data for data from 1980 to the present. Includes
winds, geopotential heights, temperature, humidity, sea level pressure, SST, surface pressure.
Data can be averaged over time. Means, climatology and anomalies can be plotted. >
<meta keywords=Plot Climate Interactive Weather Winds Temperature Mean Climatology Anomalies>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<form method=POST action="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cgi-bin/fnl.pl">
<center>
<a href="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov">
<IMG alt="Climate Diagnostics Center" SRC="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/banner.gif"></a>
</center>
<h1>Atmospheric Variables Plotting Page</h1>
<font size=3>Plot the NCEP daily analysis data, OLR, and Reynolds SST data. Data coverage is 
from 1980 to the present. You have the option of averaging the last n days. Beware that the more days are averaged, the longer the plot will take.  Climatology is based on a 5 day running mean of the annual cycle (based on 1979-1995). Anomalies are formed by subtracting this daily climatology<p>
For more information on an option, select the "?" next to the option.</font>
<p>
<hr>
<font size=4>Daily plot will take between 12 and 30 seconds depending on machine load. </font>
<hr>
<ol>
<p><li><a href=http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/HistData/plot_help.html#1><img src=/cdc_images/blue_question.gif 
alt=HELP align=bottom></a> Enter <b>EITHER</b> first date and last date <b>OR</b> first date and number of days <b>OR</b> last date and number of days.<br> Default is last available day for date and 1 day (week) for number of days in average<blockquote><input type="text" name="date1" size=6> to <input type="text" name="date2" size=6> Enter beginning date [yymmdd] and/or ending date [yymmdd] <br>
<input type="text" name="days" size=3> Enter number of days in average (or weeks for Reynolds SST). <b>Default is 1</b></blockquote>
<li><a href=http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/HistData/plot_help.html#2><img src=/cdc_images/blue_question.gif 
alt=HELP align=bottom></a> Which variable? <select name="var">
<option>Geopotential height
<option>Eddy Height
<option>Zonal wind
<option>Meridonal wind
<option>Vector Winds
<option>Air temperature
<option>Relative humidity (to 300mb only)
<option>Sea level pressure
<option>Surface pressure
<option>Tropospheric temperature
<option>Tropospheric pressure
<option>OLR
<option>Reynolds SST
</select>

<li>Analysis level?
<select name="level">
<option>1000mb
<option>850mb
<option>700mb
<option>500mb
<option>400mb
<option>300mb
<option>250mb
<option>200mb
<option>150mb
<option>100mb
<option>70mb
<option>50mb
<option>surface
</select>
<p>

<li><a href=http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/HistData/plot_help.html#4><img src=/cdc_images/blue_question.gif 
alt=HELP align=bottom></a> Plot type?
<blockquote>
<input type="radio" name="type" value="0" checked>Mean
<input type="radio" name="type" value="1" >Anomaly
<input type="radio" name="type" value="2" >Climatology
</blockquote>
<li><a href=http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/HistData/plot_help.html#5><img src=/cdc_images/blue_question.gif 
alt=HELP align=bottom></a> Map Projection <select name="proj">
<option>Northern Hemisphere
<option>USA
<option>ALL
<option>Tropics
<option>Indian Pacific
<option>Custom
</select>
<blockquote>
<a href=http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/HistData/plot_help.html#6><img src=/cdc_images/blue_question.gif 
alt=HELP align=bottom></a> If CUSTOM:<br>
 Enter lowest lat (-90 to 90) <input type="text" name="xlat1" size=3> 
 Enter highest lat (-90 to 90) <input type="text" name="xlat2" size=3> <br>
 Enter western most longitude (0 to 360) <input type="text" name="xlon1" size=4> 
 Enter eastern most longitude (0 to 360) <input type="text" name="xlon2" size=4> <br>
 Chose projection for CUSTOM:
<select name="custproj">
<option> Cylindrical Equidistant 
<option> Northern Hemisphere Polar Stereographic
<option> Southern Hemisphere Polar Stereographic
</select>
</blockquote>
<li><a href=http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/HistData/plot_help.html#7><img src=/cdc_images/blue_question.gif 
alt=HELP align=bottom></a> Color Scheme
<select name="colors">
<option>Color Range based on current plot
<option>Color Range forced to be consistent (this may not work on the web)
</select>
<li><a href=http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/HistData/plot_help.html#8><img src=/cdc_images/blue_question.gif 
alt=HELP align=bottom></a> Plot contour Labels?
<blockquote>
<input type="radio" name="label" value="0" checked>No
<input type="radio" name="label" value="1">Yes
</blockquote>
<li> Scale Plot Size(%) <input type="text" name="scale" size=3>  (default is 100%)
</ol>
