<html>
<head>
<title>CDC Map Room</title>
</head>
<body>
<center>
<a href="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov">
<img alt="Climate Diagnostics Center" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/banner.gif"></a>
</center>
<h1>CDC Map Room</h1>
<hr>
<b>These products are not guaranteed to be
updated on a regular basis.  They are intended to
serve as examples of our ongoing work.  Please contact
Klaus Weickmann (<i>kmw@cdc.noaa.gov</i>) for more
information on the CDC maproom.</b>
<hr>
The CDC Map Room consists of a mix of short-term 
operational weather products
available from the National Meteorological Center 
(e.g., via Unidata) and
long-term research-oriented climate products 
produced from a variety of in-house
data sets.  The Map Room is part of CDC's real time 
climate monitoring project
whose major goals are:
<ol>
<li>Disseminate global climate products depicting 
slow oscillations of the climate
system (~>30 days).
<li>Interpret the current state of the climate system using
El Ni&ntilde;o/Southern Oscillation (ENSO) as a framework. 
<li>Produce experimental predictions of important variables
describing the slow
climate oscillations (e.g., Pacific/Indian Ocean 
sea surface temperatures,
tropical convection, etc.).  
<li>Transfer useful monitoring and forecasting 
products to NMC's Climate Analysis
Center for public dissemination.  
</ol>
The experimental climate effort involves mostly global datasets but there is
also a regional component that focuses on the evolving climate over the
Americas, including circulation, precipitation, storm tracks, etc.  The initial
set of products available for viewing illustrates some preliminary ideas under
(1) above.<p>

<hr><b>
<h2><a name="products">CDC Map Room Graphical Products</a></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="/~map/maproom/text/weather_products.shtml">
             Weather Products</a>
<li><a href="/~map/maproom/text/climate_products.shtml">
             Climate Products</a><p>
</ul>

<hr>
<h2><a name="stats">Statistics and Log Files</a></h2>
<ul>
<li>WWW Access To CDC's Map Room Pages
   <ul>
   <li><a href="/~map/maproom/LOGS/current_stats.html">
                Access Stats - Current Month</a>
   <li><a href="/~map/maproom/LOGS/previous_stats.html">
                Access Stats - Previous Month</a>
   </ul>
</ul>
<hr>
<address>
