<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Boulder Colorado Climatology Weather Data</TITLE>
<!-- Changed by: Cathy Smith, 19-Oct-1996 -->
<Meta name=Complete links to Boulder daily and monthly temperature, precipitation, and snowfall. Information also available on nearby Colorado data and miscellaneous variables such as snowpack, streamflow, tornadoes, wind, and thunderstorms >
<meta keywords=Boulder Colorado Climate temperature precipitation snowfall data winds floods weather>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<center>
<a href="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov">
<IMG alt="Climate Diagnostics Center" SRC="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/banner.gif"></a>
</center>
<hr>
<h3>Check out these interactive climate pages</h3>
<UL>
<li><A HREF="rank.html"><b>Display rankings</a> for Boulder monthly mean data</b>
<li> <A HREF="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/USclimate"><B>United States climate page </a>with a point and click interface that displays the climate of many cities across the country</B>
<li><B>Direct link to <A HREF="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/~cas/Climo/polys/colorado.html">Colorado interactive climate page</B></A>
</UL>
<hr>
<center><H1>Boulder Climate and Weather Data</H1></center>
<ul>
<li><h3>Climatology and Daily Records</h3>
<ul>
<LI><A HREF="march.data.html" ><b>Daily: Climatology and Daily Records</b></a>: Temperature and snowfall
<li><a href="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/~cas/boulder.daily.plot.html"><b>Selected Graphics:</b></a>Daily and monthly means<IMG alt="NEW" SRC="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/new.gif">
<li>Obtain file of <b><a href="getdata.html">Boulder daily data </b></a>
</ul>
<p>
<li><H3>Temperatures</H3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="data.daily.html" ><b>Daily: Weather Observations </b>1948-<B>October 1996</B> temperature, rainfall and snow</A>
<br>
<LI><A HREF="Boulder.mm.html" ><b>Monthly: Mean Temperature </b>from 1897 to <b>October 1996</b></A>

<LI><A HREF="Boulder.mm.maxt.html"><b>Monthly: Maximum Temperature </b>from 1893-<B>October 1996</B></A>

<LI><A HREF="Boulder.mm.mint.html"><b>Monthly: Minimum Temperature </b>from 1893-<B>October 1996</B></A>

<LI><A HREF="boulder.daysgt90.html"><b>Monthly: Days greater than 90F in a month  </b>from 1990-<B>October 1996</B></A>
<LI><A HREF="freeze.html">First Day of Frost in Boulder</A>
</UL>
<p>
<li><H3>Precipitation and Snowfall</H3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="Boulder.mm.precip.html"><b>Monthly: Precipitation </a></b>from 1893 to <B>October 1996</B>
<LI><A HREF="bouldersnow.html"><b>Monthly: Snowfall </a></b>1889 to <b>October 1996</b>
<Li><A HREF="firstsnow.html">First day of snow in Boulder</A>
<Li><A HREF="lastsnow.html">Last day of snow in Boulder</A>
</UL>
<p>
<li><H3>Boulder Severe Weather and Thunderstorms</H3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="Boulder.flood.html">Boulder Area Flood Info</A>
<LI><A HREF="wind.html">Boulder Area Wind Info</A>
<LI><A HREF="thunder.test.html"><b>Monthly: Thunderstorm frequency</A></b> from 1990-<B>October 1996</B>
</UL>
<p>
<li><H3>Other Related Boulder Information</H3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="boulder.st.hx.html">Boulder Station history</A>
<LI><A HREF="boulder.sunset.html">Boulder Sunrise/Sunset times and length of twilight</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.ifa.hawaii.edu/ifa/astronomy/moon96.html">Phase of the moon </a>(from the Hawaii astronomical site)
<LI><A HREF="http://thunder.met.fsu.edu/~nws/srss.html">Sunrise, Sunset, lunar phase and moonrise/moonset times</a> for anywhere in the United States from the U.S. Naval Observatory.
<LI><A HREF="http://webserver.cr.usgs.gov/station_data/co_realtime/station_html/06730200.html">Boulder Creek Streamflow</a>
</UL>
<p>
<li><H3>Other Regional and Colorado Climate Information</H3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="snowpack.html">Up-to-date Colorado snowpack and River basin data: updated through <B>12/26/96</B></A>
<LI><A HREF="http://ulysses.atmos.colostate.edu/">Colorado Climate Center </a>has historical Colorado station data, standardized precip maps and daily realtime data for selected stations. A good source of Colorado data!
<LI><A HREF="http://execpc.com/~edi/nab/nab.html">Latest Allergy Information </a> from the National Allergy Bureau.
<LI><A HREF="tornado.html">Tornadoes in Colorado and Boulder</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://webserver.cr.usgs.gov/station_data/co_realtime/html/CWC_MAP.html">Colorado Streamflow map</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://webserver.cr.usgs.gov/water_data.html">Colorado Water Data </a>(historical and realtime).
</UL>
<p>
<li><H3>Complete links to up-to-date Boulder weather and forecasts</H3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://bcn.boulder.co.us/weather/center.html">The BCN Weather Center</A>
</UL>
<p>
<li><H3>Detailed Current Climate Analysis</H3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/~jtb/maproom/"> The CDC maproom page</A>
</UL>
<P>
<li><H3>Data Sources</H3>

Note- I am often asked for help in obtaining data. While I'm happy to try
to help, there is a substantial collection of data available from the 
<A HREF="http://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/">National Climate Data Center (NCDC) </A>including monthly and daily data for
various sites throughout the US. State climatologists and regional climate centers (listed in the FAQ below) would be helpful 
for the type of questions I usually get asked. (I have put together a list of <a href="climatecenters.html">state climate centers that have web pages</a> ).  Also, the <A HREF="http://www.ucar.edu/dss/faq/">meteorological FAQ</a> maintained at 
NCAR by Ilana Stern is a great source of info and has most of the 
available meteorological data in the world listed.  
<p>
Sources of data for this Boulder page include NCDC, NOAA Cooperative site 
daily observations, the National Storm Data Report, the National Resource
Conservations Service, , daily
data for 1948-1990 provided by Klaus Wolter (CDC) and the Colorado climate center and summaries of daily data for the last 100 years listed in the Colorado Daily prepared by Bill Callihan. More data (especially ANY wind data) is always welcome!!
<p>
</ul>
<b>Pages are for curiosity only; as in life, there are no guarantees.
If you notice any errors, I'll correct them ASAP</b>
<hr>
	<address>
The URL for this document is: http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/~cas/boulder.html
