<HTML>
<HEAD>
<title>Clickable Map of US States Climate page</title>
<!-- Changed by: Cathy Smith, 24-Jan-1996 -->
<meta name=Interactive access to climate information for stations throughout 
the United States and it's possessions. Interface is point and click to 
state maps and cities on those maps. The average daily climatology for
temperature (maximum and minimum), precipitation and snowfall are shown. 
Information on average winds, percent sunshine and percent change of rain
are shown if available. The distribution of monthly means for temperature
and precipitation are also accessible, both in ranked list form for 1961-1990
( until Dec 1995 for precipitation) and in plot form >
<meta keywords=Climate Weather United States temperature precipitation monthly mean
snowfall winds sunshine map states station data >
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<center>
<a href="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov">
<IMG alt="Climate Diagnostics Center" SRC="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/banner.gif"></a>
</center>
<center><H1>United States Interactive Climate Page</H1></center>
<font size=4>
<IMG alt="New" SRC="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/new.gif">Raw monthly mean data available through "Rankings" page.</a><br>
<IMG alt="New" SRC="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/new.gif">Monthly means through June 1996 now available!</a><p>
<hr>
This web site provides easy access to climatologies
for cities throughout the US and its possessions. Simply click
on the state you are interested in and then click on the city name (or
the bullet that indicates the city's location).  You will then get a
plot of the daily average climate for that city including maximum and 
minimum temperature, precipitation and snowfall. There is also the option of examining the monthly mean rankings for time period. Select the "rankings" button over the state plot for this option.
</font>
<hr>
<H2>Choose access method</H2>

<UL>
<font size=6>
<LI><a href="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/USclimate/states.fast.html">Fast lane (detailed maps)</a>:  suitable for high speed connection<p>
<LI><a href="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/USclimate/states.slow.html">Slow lane</a>: suitable for modems and high traffic times<br><p>
<LI><a href="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/USclimate/states.scroll.html">Even Slower lane (text access)</a>: when even the slow lane is a little too slow<br>
</font>

</UL>
<hr size=4>
<h3>Useful Pages:</h3>
<font size=5>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/~cas/Climo/polys/glossary.html">Glossary of terms, data, and project construction details</a></br>
<li><a href="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/~cas/Climo/polys/websites.html">List of related climate and educational websites</a><br>
<li><a href="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/USclimate/climate.error.html">Error reporting form </a></br>
</ul>
</font>
<p>
