<title>CDC's NMC Reanalysis Home Page</title>
</head>
<body>
<div align=center>
<a href=http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/>
<img src=/cdc_images/banner.gif alt=" "></a><br>
<h1>The <a href = "http://www.ncep.noaa.gov/">NCEP</a>/<a href = 
"http://www.ucar.edu/">NCAR</a> Reanalysis Project</h1>
<h2><a href = "http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/">NOAA Climate Diagnostics Center</a></h2>
</div>

This page points you to information on the NCEP/NCAR Reanalysis project and
the implementation of a netCDF-based, Internet-accessible, data service
at NOAA CDC for this set of data products.<P>

<hr>

<H2>NCEP/NCAR Reanalysis at CDC:</H2><p>
<H1><A HREF="../data.nmc.reanalysis.html">Here's what is currently available on-line.</a>  Please read the <a href="problems.shtml"> problem list </a>.</H1>



<UL>
<LI><strong>Status</strong>

<UL>
<LI><A HREF="status.shtml">Current project status</A> 
<em>(Nov 18, 1996)</em>

<LI><A HREF="problems.shtml">Reanalysis problems list</A> 
<em>(Nov 15, 1996)</em> 

</UL>

<LI><strong>Inventory/specifications</strong>
<UL>

<LI><A HREF="../data.nmc.reanalysis.html">Description of data on-line at
CDC</A> <em>(Aug 22, 1996)</em>

<LI><A HREF="netcdf.html">Specifications for netCDF files</A>
including estimated dataset sizes 
<em>(Jun 27, 1995)</em>


<LI><A HREF="FileList.html">Inventory of the original GRIB files</A> 
<em>(Jan  5, 1996)</em>

</UL>

<LI><strong>Compatible software</strong>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc/netopen/netsubs_read.shtml">netopen FORTRAN library</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc/cdc_software.html#crdtools">CRDtools</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.pmel.noaa.gov/ferret/home.html">FERRET</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://tao.atmos.washington.edu/freud/">Freud</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://grads.iges.org/grads/head.html">GrADS </A> use <a href="ftp://grads.iges.org/beta/">Version 1.6 Beta 4</a> to read our netCDF files.
<LI><A HREF="ftp://ftp.pmel.noaa.gov/eps/matlab/">MATLAB - MEXEPS</A>
<LI><b>xgplot/ngplot</b> (custom plotting with GUI or scripts) - contact Matt Newman (men@cdc.noaa.gov)
</UL>

<LI><A
<li><a href=/ncep_reanalysis/>Electronic Atlas of derived NCEP Reanalysis products</a>
</UL>
</UL>

