<html>
<head>
<Title> Re-emergence Mechanism Caption> </Title>
</head>
<body>

<img src="reemerge.mech.gif" alt="Illustration of re-emergence mechanism">
<P>

Observed and Simulated lead/lag correlations at weather station P in the
North Pacific (50N, 145W) between temperature anomalies in the base layer,
45-55 m in August, and temperature anomalies in 5 m increments for the
previous and following 8 months. The simulated field is obtained from a 
500 year simulation in which a mixed layer ocean model forced by a 
statistical model of atmospheric conditions at OWS P. <P>

The re-emergence mechanism is indicated by the relatively high 
correlation values that extend in a "U" shape from the surface layer in 
spring to the summer seasonal thermocline and returning to the surface in 
winter.  At P the descending branch appears to be stronger than the 
return branch. <P>
<address>
The URL for this document is: http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc/overview/9596/reemerge.mech.caption.html
<br>
<strong>
<a href="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/">NOAA-CIRES Climate Diagnostics Center</a> <br>
</strong>
Last updated: Tuesday, 29-Oct-96 17:51:11 MST
<br>
</address>

