src="images/buttons/products.gif" height=31 width=122
alt="Climate Products"></a><a

href="rel_links.html"><img
align=top border=0
src="images/buttons/links.gif" height=31 width=99
alt="Related Links"></a><a

href="theindex.html"><img
align=top border=0
src="images/buttons/index.gif" height=31 width=57
alt="Index"></a>
</nobr>
<hr>
<h1 align=center>Research</h1>
<a
href="pacs.html"><img
align=left
alt="" 
src="images/smallpacs.gif">

PACS - PanAmerican Climate Studies program.</a>
The goal of this NOAA project is to improve the skill of operational
seasonal to interannual climate prediction over the Americas.  We are
investigating radiative and hydrological processes over the eastern
tropical Pacific and the Americas using a combination of satellite
data sets over several spectral bands.

<br clear=left><hr>
<a
href="ocean_winds.html"><img
align=left
alt=""
src="images/smallwinds.gif">

Ocean Winds.</a>.
This project involves observation and modeling studies
of surface wind speed and direction using microwave emission and
backscatter from the ocean surface.

<br clear=left><hr>
<a
href="game.html"><img
align=left
alt=""
src="images/smallgamelogo.gif">

GAME - GEWEX Asian Monsoon Experiment.</a>
The goal of this project is to provide a better understanding of the
key physical processes for the onset and maintenance of the monsoon
over southeast Asia and southern China leading to improved
predictions.

<br clear=left><hr>

<a
href="gvap.html"><img
alt=""
align=left
src="images/smallgvap.gif">

GVaP - Global Energy and Water Cycle Experiment (GEWEX) Water Vapor Project.</a>
Using satellite observations, we are working to improve our
understanding of the role of atmospheric water vapor and its
variability in global meteorological, hydrological, and climatological
processes.

<br clear=left><hr>

<a
href="pathfinder.html"><img
alt=""
align=left
src="images/smallpathfinder.gif">

TOVS Pathfinder.</a>
This project involves the production and analysis of a TOVS Pathfinder
radiance data set to help us better understand the changes in the
atmospheric hydrological cycle resulting from boundary forcing over
seasonal to interannual time scales.

<br clear=left><hr>

<a
href="other.html"><img
alt=""
align=left
src="images/smallgoes_composite.gif">

Other research projects.</a>

These include a variety of currently unfunded projects being
investigated for future funding opportunities or in conjunction with
other scientists and/or science organizations.

<br clear=left>
<P>
<img alt="" src="images/go_back.gif"><a href="">Satellite home page.</a>
