<title>
CDC FY 97 Plans
</title>
</head>
<body>
<center>
<a href=http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/><img src=/cdc_images/banner.gif
alt="NOAA/ERL Climate Diagnostics Center"></a>
<h2>FY97 Program Information and Operating Plan</h2>
<p>
<em><a href=/cdc/overview/>Contents</a></em> |
<em><a href=/cdc/overview/background.shtml>Background</a></em> | 
<em><a href=index.shtml>Recent Accomplishments</a></em> |
<em><a href=/cdc/overview/9596/>FY95/96 Information</a>
</em><p>
</center>
<hr>
<h2>ADVANCE SHORT-TERM WARNING AND FORECAST SERVICES</h2>
<dl>
<dt>
<h3>OBJECTIVE: Enhance Observations and Predictions</h3>
<dd>
<img src=/cdc_images/blueball.gif alt="o">
<em><strong>Performance Measure:</strong></em>  
Assess the utility of the NCEP ensemble forecasting system to predict
the skill of ensemble means and the utility of probabilistic forecasts
obtained from the ensemble, particularly for extreme events.
<p>
<img src=/cdc_images/greenball.gif alt="o">
<em><strong>Milestone:</strong></em>  
Verification scores and statistical tests will be computed for the
preceding year of ensemble forecasts.  (Q2, J. Whitaker)
</dl>

<h2>IMPLEMENT SEASONAL TO INTERANNUAL CLIMATE FORECASTS</h2>
<dl>
<dt>
<h3>OBJECTIVE: Conduct Research For Improved Climate Predictions
</h3>
<dd>
<img src=/cdc_images/blueball.gif alt="o">
<em><strong>Performance Measure:</strong></em>  
Assess the global climate system's response to the El 
Ni&ntilde;o/Southern Oscillation (ENSO).
<p>
<img src=/cdc_images/greenball.gif alt="o">
<em><strong>Milestone:</strong></em>  
Perform a suite of modeling studies to evaluate physical and
dynamical response to the El-Ni&ntilde;o/Southern Oscillation.  The paradigm of the
climate signal associated with ENSO is of a linear response with anomalies
during the warm El Ni&ntilde;o phase opposite those during the cold 
La Ni&ntilde;a phase.
Emerging observational evidence suggests appreciable non-linearities.
(Q3, M. Hoerling, P. Sardeshmukh)
<p>
<img src=/cdc_images/blueball.gif alt="o">
<em><strong>Performance Measure:</strong></em>  
Determine the sensitivity of the North American climate to details of
tropical Pacific SST forcing.
<p>
<img src=/cdc_images/greenball.gif alt="o">
<em><strong>Milestone:</strong></em>  
Execute a hierarchy of atmospheric GCM simulations using progressive
degradations of tropical SST anomaly patterns.  The analysis will establish
the practical importance of forecasting the details of that SST forcing in
coupled climate models.
(Q4, M. Hoerling, P. Sardeshmukh)
<p>
<img src=/cdc_images/blueball.gif alt="o">
<em><strong>Performance Measure:</strong></em>  
Create a simple model of extra tropical low frequency (LF) variability
using a parameterization of high frequency (HF) synoptic eddy variability.
<p>
<img src=/cdc_images/greenball.gif alt="o">
<em><strong>Milestone:</strong></em>  
Quantify how the modeled LF variability is modified when the HF eddy
flux parameterization is included, as opposed to parameterizing the HF eddy
fluxes as stochastic noise, and assess the degree to which the modeled LF
variability resembles that observed.  (Q2, J. Whitaker)
<p>
<img src=/cdc_images/blueball.gif alt="o">
<em><strong>Performance Measure:</strong></em>  
Document the mean variability of surface fluxes in the GFDL atmospheric
general circulation model (GCM).
<p>
<img src=/cdc_images/greenball.gif alt="o">
<em><strong>Milestone:</strong></em>  
Diagnose the variability of air-sea heat fluxes, an important source
of energy for both the atmosphere and ocean, from synoptic (weekly) to
interannual time scales.  (Q2, M. Alexander)
<p>
<img src=/cdc_images/blueball.gif alt="o">
<em><strong>Performance Measure:</strong></em>  
Process subsurface ocean temperature records and examine them for
winter-to-winter reemergence of SST anomalies.
<p>
<img src=/cdc_images/greenball.gif alt="o">
<em><strong>Milestone:</strong></em>  
Examine the extent to which thermal anomalies, created during winter
in the relatively deep ocean mixed layer, remain intact in the summer
seasonal thermocline and then re-emerge at the surface in the following
winter in the North Atlantic and North Pacific ocean basins.  
(Q4, M. Alexander) 
<p>
<img src=/cdc_images/blueball.gif alt="o">
<em><strong>Performance Measure:</strong></em>  
Convene a meeting of U. S. participants in the international GEWEX Water
Vapor Project (GVaP).
<p>
<img src=/cdc_images/greenball.gif alt="o">
<em><strong>Milestone:</strong></em>  
Convene a meeting at the AMS 1997 annual meeting to discuss how and
whether a new hypothesis of the climatic effect of atmospheric water vapor
should be a major focus of a U.S. GVaP effort.  This U.S. GVaP meeting will
be a follow-up to the international GVaP meeting to take place in Geneva in
November 1996. 	(Q2, J. Bates)
<p>
<img src=/cdc_images/blueball.gif alt="o">
<em><strong>Performance Measure:</strong></em>  
Assess and suggest improvements to the tropical water cycle of the
atmospheric model component of NCEP's atmosphere-ocean forecast system.
<p>
<img src=/cdc_images/greenball.gif alt="o">
<em><strong>Milestone:</strong></em>  
Rigorously assess the atmospheric component of the NECP
atmosphere-ocean forecast system by simulating the observed seasonal and
interannual variability of the atmospheric hydrological cycle.  A particular
emphasis will be placed on assessing and improving the ability of the
atmospheric model to accurately simulate the observed variability of upper
tropospheric water vapor.  (Q4, J. Bates)
<p>
<img src=/cdc_images/blueball.gif alt="o">
<em><strong>Performance Measure:</strong></em>  
Assess the spatial and temporal characteristics of climatic fluctuations
as a function of elevation.
<p>
<img src=/cdc_images/greenball.gif alt="o">
<em><strong>Milestone:</strong></em>  
Complete a special monograph on the record of climatic variations
with height in comparison with hemispheric and global 
indices.  (Q4, H. Diaz)
</dl>

<h2>DOCUMENT, PREDICT, AND ASSESS DECADAL-TO CENTENNIAL CLIMATE CHANGE</h2>
<dl>
<dt>
<h3>OBJECTIVE: Ensure a Long-Term Climate Record</h3>
<dd>
<img src=/cdc_images/blueball.gif alt="o">
<em><strong>Performance Measure:</strong></em>  
Complete Comprehensive Ocean Atmosphere Data Set (COADS) Release 1b
1950-59 observations required for Global Reanalysis.
<p>
<img src=/cdc_images/greenball.gif alt="o">
<em><strong>Milestone:</strong></em>  
	This data set of individual surface marine observations from ships
and buoys is an important input for the NCEP/NCAR Global Re-Analysis
Project.  Update of the 1950-59 period as part of COADS Release 1b.  (Q4,
S. Woodruff) 
<p>
<dt>
<h3>OBJECTIVE: Furnish Prediction, Assessment, and
Human Impacts Information</h3>
<dd>
<img src=/cdc_images/blueball.gif alt="o">
<em><strong>Performance Measure:</strong></em>  
Increase the utility of CDC's environmental data and information
resources for scientists and the general public.
<p>
<img src=/cdc_images/greenball.gif alt="o">
<em><strong>Milestone:</strong></em>  
Reorganize and redesign CDC's web site to improve functionality and
simplify access for all Internet users.  (Q2, D. Mock, J. Collins)
</dl>
<address>
