<hr>
My primary research focuses on the application of remote sensing technology
to the estimation of atmospheric and ocean surface parameters for the study
of climate variability and global change.  Current research projects involve
the study of climate-scale hydrological processes using data from
satellite-based passive microwave radiometers and other satellite data
sources.

