<h2>Education</h2>

<ul>
<li> B.S., Bio-Chemistry, University of Colorado, May 1993.
</ul>

<hr>
<h2>Related Links</h2>

<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/~jdg/home.html">Personal home page</a><br>
<li><a href="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/~jdg/vitae.html">Vitae</a><br>
<li><a href="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/~jdg/publications.shtml">Publications</a><br>
<li><a href="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/~jdg/publications.shtml#presentations">Presentations</a><br>
</ul>

<hr>
	John provides support for the research of Dr. Brant Liebmann and Dr.
Harry Hendon. He retreives, filters and otherwise prepares data, runs various
statistical analyses and prepares plots for both publication and presentation.
In addition, he runs a version of the Cane and Ghent Pacific Basin model and
helps to debug and run a version of the Baroclinic Chi Problem correction of
the NCEP reanalysis.
<p>
	John uses primarily Fortran and the NCAR Graphics package for analyzing
data and creating plots, but also uses IDL, Matlab and Kaliedagraph for 
visualization.

