<HTML>
<TITLE>Darren Jackson's curriculum vitae</TITLE>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<B>
<CENTER>
<H1>Darren Jackson</H1>
<H2><A HREF="http://cires.colorado.edu/">CIRES</A>, Campus Box 449
<BR>University of Colorado
<BR>Boulder, CO 80309
<BR>(303) 492-0683</H2>
</B>
<ADDRESS>dlj@cdc.noaa.gov</ADDRESS>
</CENTER>
<HR SIZE=5>

<DL>
<DT><H2>Research Experience:</H2>

<DD><B> Professional Research Assistant</B>, <A
HREF="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/">Climate Diagnostic Center</A>,
September 1994 - present
<BR><BR>

<img alt="o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/~dlj/images/blueball.gif">
My latest project is the TOVS Pathfinder study where we are re-calibrating and
cloud clearing all of the HIRS 1b dataset (1979-current).
<BR>

<img alt="o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/~dlj/images/blueball.gif">
I am conducting research on the distribution and variability
of global water vapor as a part of the GEWEX water vapor project (<A
HREF="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/~dlj/gvap.html">GVaP</A>,).
This research includes deriving upper tropospheric water vapor using a
16-year climatology of intercalibrated HIRS data from the NOAA-6
through NOAA-12 satellites.  Other related research includes performing
comparisons between six different global water vapor data sets in
order to assess the differences between these different data sets.
<BR>

<img alt="o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/~dlj/images/blueball.gif">
I am comparing water vapor data from The Atmospheric Model
Intercomparison Project (<A
HREF="http://www-pcmdi.llnl.gov/phillips/AMIP.html">AMIP</A>) to
SMMR precipitable water data and upper tropospheric humidity data
derived from HIRS channel 12 data.
<P>

<B> Graduate Research Assistant</B>, <A 
HREF="http://www.atmos.colostate.edu/"> Colorado State University
Atmospheric Science Department</A>, September 1989 - August 1994.
<BR><BR>

<img alt="o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/~dlj/images/blueball.gif">
The focus of my graduate research was on analyzing a climatology of
four years of precipitable water derived from SSM/I observations.  I
analyzed both temporal and spatial variablitity of precipitable water
over the global oceans.  I also described the global relationship
between SST and precipitable water.  Other research included comparing
precipitable water derived from SSM/I and TOVS.  
<cite> <br>
Thesis title: On the role of SSM/I derived precipitable water over the
globe and tropical Pacific.</cite><BR><BR>
<P>

<B> Undergraduate Research Assistant</B>,
<a HREF="http://www.public.iastate.edu/~wxintro/atmos.html">
Iowa State University Atmospheric Science Department </A> ,
September 1986 - May 1989
<BR><BR> 
<img alt="o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/~dlj/images/blueball.gif">
I assisted in the research of retrieving ozone concentrations using
satellite data.  I also assisted in the research on barotropic instability
forced by topography. 

<P>

<DT><H2>Technical skills:</H2>
<DD>

<img alt="o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/~dlj/images/blueball.gif">
Knowledge of the Unix, Unicos and VMS operating systems.<BR><BR>

<img alt="o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/~dlj/images/blueball.gif">
Experience on a variety of computer systems including IBM, SUN and
Digital workstations, Cray supercomputers, and IBM-compatible
personal computers.<BR><BR>

<img alt="o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/~dlj/images/blueball.gif">
Proficiency in using Fortran 77 and IDL.

<DT><H2>Education:</H2>
<DD>
<B> M.S. in Atmospheric Science</B>, <a href="http://www.colostate.edu/">
Colorado State University </a>, Ft. Collins, CO, December 1992.  GPA: 3.9/4.0

<BR><BR>
<B> B.S. in Meteorology</B>, <a HREF="http://www.iastate.edu/">
Iowa State University</a>, Ames, IA, May 1989.  Graduated with
Distinction and Honors. GPA: 3.7/4.0

<P>

<DT><H2>Recent/Upcoming conference papers:</H2>
<DD>

Bates, J.J., and D.L. Jackson, 1997:  Seasonal and interannual variability
of upper tropospheric humidity and clear sky outgoing longwave
radiation.  To be presented at Ninth Conference on Atmospheric
Radiation, Long Beach, CA, February 2-7, 1997.

<BR><BR>

Bates, J.J., and D.L. Jackson, 1997:  A comparison of satellite water
vapor observations with model simulations.  To be presented at Eighth
Symposium on Global Change Studies, Long Beach, CA, February 2-7, 1997.

<BR><BR>

Bates, J.J., and D.L. Jackson, 1996:  Opening windows to cool the greenhouse:
Observational evidence of a tropical water vapor balance. Presented at Second
International Conference on the Global Energy and Water Cycle,
Washington, D.C., June 17-21, 1996.

<BR><BR>

Bates, J.J., and D.L. Jackson, 1995:  Rethinking the water vapor feedback.
Presented at AGU 1995 Fall Meeting, San Francisco, CA  December 14-18, 1995.

<DT><H2>Publications:</H2>
<DD>

<HTML>
<head>
</head>
<body>
<ul>

<li>Bates, J.J., and D.L. Jackson, 1996:  A comparison of water vapor
observations with AMIP-I simulations.<I>J. Geophys Res. </I>, submitted.
<P>
<li>Bates, J.J., X. Wu, and D.L. Jackson, 1996:  Interannual variability
of upper tropospheric water vapor band brightness temperature.
<I>J. Climate </I>, <B>9</B>, 427-438. <a href="/~dlj/dljref.html#1">Abstract available.</a><P>
<li>Stephens, G.L., D.L. Jackson, and I. Wittmeyer, 1996: Global
observations of upper-tropospheric water vapor derived from TOVS
radiance data. <I>J. Climate</I>, <B>9</B>, 305-326. <a href="/~dlj/dljref.html#2">Abstract available.</a><P>
<li>Jackson, D.L., and G.L. Stephens, 1995:  A study of SSM/I derived
columnar water vapor over the global oceans. <I> J. Climate </I>,
<B>8</B>, 2025-2038. <a href="/~dlj/dljref.html#3">Abstract available.</a><P>
<li>Stephens, G.L., D.L. Jackson, and J.J. Bates, 1994:  A comparison of
SSM/I and TOVS column water vapor data over the global oceans. <I>
Meteorol. Atmos. Phys.</I>, <B>54</B>, 183-201. <a href="/~dlj/dljref.html#4">Abstract available.</a><P>
<li>Greenwald, T.J., G.L. Stephens, T.H. Vonder Haar, and D.L. Jackson,
1993:  A physical retrieval of cloud liquid water over the global
oceans using SSM/I observations. <I>J. Geophys. Res.</I>, <B>98</B>, 18,
471-18,488. <a href="/~dlj/dljref.html#5">Abstract available</a><P>
<li>Jackson, D.L., 1992:  On the role of SSM/I derived precipitable water
over the globe and tropical pacific.  M.S. Thesis, Colorado State
University, 112 pp. <a href="/~dlj/dljref.html#6">Abstract available</a><P>
<li>Tjemkes, S.A., G.L. Stephens, and D.L. Jackson, 1991:  Spacebourne
observation of columnar water vapor: SSMI observations and algorithm.
<I> J. Geophys. Res.</I>, <B>96</B>, 10,941-10,954. <a href="/~dlj/dljref.html#7">Abstract available
     .</a><P>
</ul>
