<hr>
Research Summary for Brian Mapes
<p>
Atmospheric tropical convection is the overall theme of this research.
Satellite data give a climatological overview of tropical convection,
with space and time resolution sufficiently fine to resolve the
individual cloud clusters.  Doppler radar and other meteorological
data from field experiments are used to ascertain relevant details
of the internal structure of particular precipitating cloud systems,
most notably the vertical profile of the heating rate.  Results from
these data analyses are idealized and fed into simple analytic and
numerical models, in order to clarify the detailed mechanisms
by which convective cloud heating drives tropical circulations
at spatial scales from mesoscale to planetary.

<hr>
