<TITLE>Chesley McColl's Vitae</TITLE>

<B>
<CENTER>
<H1>Chesley McColl</H1>
<H2>CIRES, Campus Box 449
<BR>University of Colorado
<BR>Boulder, CO 80309
<BR>(303) 492-7304</H2>
</B>
<ADDRESS><A HREF="mailto:ckm@cdc.noaa.gov">ckm@cdc.noaa.gov</A></ADDRESS>
</CENTER>
<HR SIZE=5>
Last updated: Monday, 06-May-96 16:09:01 MDT<br>

<DL>
<DT><H2>Present Position:</H2>

<DD><A  HREF="http://cires.colorado.edu/"><B> Cooperative Institute for
        Research in Environmental Sciences (CIRES),</B></A>
        University of Colorado, Boulder.
<BR>
<BR><B> Professional Research Assistant</B>, August 1994 - present.
<BR><BR>
	I work in the 
<A 	HREF="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/~climsat"> Climsat Group </A>, which
	uses data from environmental satellites to study climate variability. 
        Currently I am pursuing using passive microwave data from the special 
	sensor microwave/imager 
<A 	HREF="http://www.daac.msfc.nasa.gov/ssmi.html"> (SSM/I) </A> 
	to determine wind direction.  This analysis will be compared with 
	co-located <I>in situ</I> buoy wind direction data.  I am using
	several different techniques to determine wind direction.  One is 
	the use of 
<A 	HREF="WSWD/index.shtml">Neural Networks </A>. 
 	Another method is to model the total radiative transfer. And
	finally a two-dimensional variation analysis to obtain
	the wind field.
<BR><BR>
	I developed 
<A	HREF="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/~ckm/EOF/">wavelet analysis tools</A>
	to study global SST, OLR and HIRS 12 fields. 
        I have converted analysis and visualization
<A 	HREF = "http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/~climsat/khoros-programs.html">tools
</A>	within the <A HREF="http://www.khoros.unm.edu"> <B> Khoros
        2.0 Software Development Environment</B> </A>
        for detailed study of 
<A 	HREF="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/~cec/climsat.html">
	climatic satellite data </A> and SAR images.
 
<P>

<DT><H2>Previous Experience:</H2>
<DD>

