<BR><B> Member of the Technical Staff</B>, 1989-1994

<BR>	Precision Orbit Determination and Verification team leader for the TOPEX	/Poseidon project.  Responsible for the management, planning and team 
 	operations. The team studied global ocean circulation, performed
	altimeter verification and calibrations, and produced short arc orbits
	over the verification sites.  Developed software and strategies for 
	processing the GPS, laser and doris data.    
<P>
<BR><B>	University of Colorado, 
<A 	HREF="http://128.138.129.27/Home.html"> Boulder</B></A>

<BR><B> Research Assistant</B>, 1988-1989.
   
<BR>	Worked in the computational fluids department, developed a numerical 
	simulation for unsteady flows produced by an oscillating ellipse and 
	cylinder.
<P>
<BR><B> TRW: San Bernardino CA </B>
<BR><B>	Member for the Technical Staff</B>, 1986-1988
<BR>	Worked in the Concept Design and Evaluation Department, responsible for
	preliminary design activities, including the determination of concept
	feasibility, determination of design requirements and selection of
	concepts for advanced development.    
<P>
<BR><B>	University of Colorado, Boulder </B>
<BR><B>	Research Assistant</B>, 1983-1985
<BR>	Helped develop the calibration scheme for the ultra-violet experiment
	on the Solar-Mesospheric Explorer. Evaluated the safety of and sent
	commands to the satellite in real time. 
