<center><h2>CURRICULUM VITAE<br>
FOR MARY C&Eacute;CILE PENLAND</h2></center>

<hr>

<h3>Personal Data</h3><p>

<dl>
<dl>
<dd><dt>Name:
<dd><dd>Mary C&eacute;cile Penland<p>

<dd><dt>Current Position:
<dd><dd>Research Associate<sup>*</sup> since Sept. 1989<br>
<dd><dl>
<dd>		             <dd>CIRES, University of Colorado<br>
<dd>		             <dd>Boulder, CO 80309-0449<br>
<dd>		             <dd>Tel: (303) 492-4826<br>
<dd>		             <dd>FAX: (303) 492-2468<br>
<dd>		             <dd>e-mail: mcp@cdc.noaa.gov<p>
</dl>

<dd><dt>Nationality:
<dd><dd>U. S. A.
</dl>
</dl>

<p>
<font size=3><i><sup>*"</sup>Research Associate" is the standard title
given to researchers by CIRES at the University of Colorado and
does not denote a position given to a recent PhD.</i></font><p>

<hr>

<h3>Education</h3>

<ul>
<li>B.S.  Physics, Florida Atlantic Univ., Boca Raton, Fla.,  1975 (entered as Junior).
<li>M.S.  Physics, Florida Atlantic Univ., Boca Raton, Fla.,  1977.
<li>Ph.D.  Physics, The Univ. of Texas at Austin, Austin, Tx., 1984 (GPA: 4.0).
</ul>

<hr>

<h3>Previous Professional Employment</h3>

<ul>
<li>
Dept. Atmospheric Sciences, University of California, Los Angeles, CA
90024<br>
Sept., 1988 - Sept., 1989, Recipient, Career Advancement Award (NSF grant
ATM88-08797).<p>

<li>
Dept. Physics, California State University, Long Beach, CA 90650<br>
Aug., 1987-June, 1988, Lecturer<p>

<li>
Max-Planck-Institut f&uuml;r Meteorologie, Hamburg, Bundesrepublik
Deutschland, Jan. 7,1985-March 31,1987, Postdoc. Fellow  (jointly with
Universit&eacute; Libre de Bruxelles, Brussels, Belgium, April 1, 1986-Dec.
31,1986).<p>

<li>
Applied Research Lab., The Univ. of Texas at Austin, Austin, TX, 
1980-1984, Research Assistant.<p>

<li>
Dept. of Physics, The Univ. of Texas at Austin, Austin, TX, 1977-1980,
Assistant Instructor.<p>

<li>
Dept. of Physics, Florida Atlantic Univ., 1975-1977, Teaching
Assistant.<p>

</ul>

<hr>

<h3>Membership in Professional Societies</h3>

<ul>
<li>	American Meteorological Society
<li>	American Geophysical Union
<li>	American Institute of Physics
</ul>

<hr>

<h3>Areas of Specialization</h3>

<ul>
<li>	Stochastic processes applied to climate modeling
<li>	Climate dynamics
<li>	Stochastic differential equations
</ul>

<hr>

<h3>Publications</h3>

<html>
<head>
<title></title>
</head>
<body>
<ul>

Monthly contributor to <i>Forecasters' Forum </i>section of "Climate
Diagnostics Bulletin," National Weather Service, NMC, Washington DC.
<a href="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/~cas/Cecile.forecast.html">Current
 forecast.</A> <p>

Seasonal contributor to "Experimental Long-lead Forecast Bulletin," National
Weather Service, NMC, CPC, Prediction Branch, Washington DC.<p>

<li>Penland, C., and L. Matrosova, 1997: "Prediction of tropical Atlantic sea surface temperatures using Linear Inverse Modeling," <i>J. Climate</i>, submitted.<p>

<li>Newman, M., P. D. Sardeshmukh and C. Penland, 1997: "Stochastic forcing 
of the wintertime extratropical flow," <i>J. Atmos. Sci</i>, <b>54</b>, 435-455.<p>

<li>Penland, C., 1996: "A stochastic model of IndoPacific sea surface 
temperature anomalies," <i>Physica D</i>, <b>98</b>, 534-558.<p>

<li>Alexander, M. A., and C. Penland, 1996: "Variability in a mixed layer
ocean model driven by stochastic atmospheric forcing," <i>J. Climate</i>,
<b>9</b>, 2424-2442.<p>

<li>Penland, C., 1996: "On the phase-locking between El Ni&ntilde;o and 
the annual cycle," <i>Proc. 20th Climate Diagnostics Workshop</i>, 
Seattle, WA, 23-27 Oct., 1995. U. S. Dept. Commerce. Springfield, VA.<p>

<li>Penland, C., and P. D. Sardeshmukh, 1995: "The optimal growth of
tropical sea surface temperature anomalies," <i>J. Climate</i>, <b>8</b>,
1999-2024.<p>

<li>Penland, C., and P. D. Sardeshmukh, 1995: "Error and sensitivity
analysis of geophysical systems," <i>J. Climate</i>, <b>8</b>, 1988-
1998.<p>

<li>Penland, C., and P. Sardeshmukh, 1995: "Uncertainty analysis of a
linear system," <i>Proc. 19h Climate Diagnostics Workshop</i>, College
Park MD, Nov. 13-18, 1994, U. S. Dept. Commerce. Springfield, VA.<p>

<li>Alexander, M., and C. Penland 1995: "Variability in a mixed-layer
model of the upper ocean driven by stochastic atmospheric surface
conditions," <i>Proc. 19h Climate Diagnostics Workshop</i>, College Park
MD, Nov. 13-18, 1994, U. S. Dept. Commerce. Springfield, VA.<p>

<li>Newman, M., P. Sardeshmukh, and C. Penland 1995: "Stochastic forcing
of low frequency variability," <i>Proc. 19h Climate Diagnostics
Workshop</i>, College Park MD, Nov. 13-18, 1994, U. S. Dept. Commerce.
Springfield, VA.<p>

<li>Poveda, G., and C. Penland, 1994: "Predicci&oacuten de caudales medios
en Colombia usando Modelaci&oacuten Lineal Inversa," <i>Proc. XVI Congreso
Latinoamericano de Hydraulica</i>, Santiago, Chile, IAHR, November 1994.<p>

<li>Penland, C., And L. Matrosova, 1994: "A balance condition for
stochastic numerical models with application to the El Ni&ntilde;o -
Southern Oscillation," <i>J. Climate</i>, <b>7</b>, 1352-1372.<p>

<li>Penland, C., and P. D. Sardeshmukh, 1994: "Nonmodal growth of tropical
sea surface temperatures," <i>Proc. 6th Conf. on Climate Variations</i>,
Nashville, Jan. 23-28, 1994, Amer. Met. Soc. Boston.<p>

<li>Penland, C., and L. Matrosova, 1994: "An Empirical-Dynamical Model of
Sea Surface Temperatures," <i>Proc. 18th Climate Diagnostics Workshop</i>,
Boulder, Nov. 1-5, 1993, U. S. Dept. Commerce. Springfield, VA.<p>

<li>Penland, C., and M. Ghil, 1993: "Forecasting Northern Hemisphere 700mb
Geopotential Height Anomalies using Empirical Normal Modes," <i>Monthly Weather
Review</i>,  <b>121</b>, 2355-2371.<p>

<li>Penland, C., and T. Magorian, 1993: "Prediction of Ni&ntilde;o 3
Sea-surface Temperature Anomalies using Linear Inverse Modeling,"<i>J.
Climate</i>, <b>6</b>, 1067-1075.<p>

<li>Garc&iacute;a, A., D. Morris, J. Stroh, and C. Penland, 1992:
"Modeling Complex Phenomena in Fluids," . In <i>Modeling Complex
Phenomena</i>, Proc. Third Woodward Conf., San Jos&eacute;, April
12-13,1991, Ed. L. Lam, Springer Verlag, New York (reviewed).<p>

<li>Penland, C., and T. Magorian, 1991: "Prediction of Ni&ntilde;o 3
Sea-surface Temperature Anomalies using Linear Inverse Modeling,"
<i>Proceedings 16h Annual Climate Diagnostics Workshop</i>, pg 354.<p>

<li>Penland, C., and M. Ghil, 1991: "Deterministic Teleconnections and
'Random' Forcing by Transient Eddies,"  <i>Proceedings Eighth Conference
on Atmospheric and Oceanic Waves and Stability</i>, Denver.<u></u><p>

<li>Penland, C., M. Ghil, and K. Weickmann, 1991: "Adaptive Filtering and
Maximum Entropy Spectra, with Application to Changes in Atmospheric
Angular Momentum," <i>Journal of Geophysical Research</i>, <b>96</b>,
22659 - 22671.<p>

<li>Garc&iacute;a, A., and C. Penland, 1991: "Fluctuating Hydrodynamics
and Principal Oscillation Pattern Analysis," <i>Journal of Statistical
Physics</i>, <b>64</b>, 1121-1132.<p>

<li>Penland, C., and M Ghil, 1990: "Principal Oscillation Patterns used in
Forecasting,", <i>Proceedings 15th Annual Climate Diagnostics
Workshop</i>, pg 355.<p>

<li>Penland, C., and M. Ghil, 1989: "Use of Principal Oscillation Patterns
in Forecasting," <i>Proceedings, 11th Conference on Probability and
Statistics in Atmospheric Sciences</i>, Monterrey.<p>

<li>Penland, C, 1989: "Random Forcing and Forecasting using Principal
Oscillation Pattern Analysis," <i>Monthly Weather Review</i>,
<b>117</b>, 2165-2185.<p>

<li>Penland, C., 1988: "The Distribution of Random Segment Lengths,"
<i>Geophysical Research Letters</i>, <b>15</b>, 1405-1408.<p>

<li>Von Storch, H., P. Lemke, and C. Penland, 1987: "Principal Oscillation
Pattern Analysis of Sea Ice Data," Report for the European Community,
Max-Planck-Institut f&uuml;r Meteorologie.<p>

<li>Penland, C., 1985: "Acoustic Normal Mode Propagation Through a
Three-Dimensional Internal Wave Field," J<i>. Acoust. Soc. Am</i>.
<b>78</b>, 1356-1365.<p>

<li>Penland, C., 1983: "The Interplay of Absorption and Internal
Wave-Induced Mode Coupling in Seawater," <i>Proceedings of the Stochastic
Modeling Workshop</i>, held at Naval Research Lab. (NRL), Wash. DC.<p>

<li>Koch, R. A., C. Penland, P. J. Vidmar, and K. Hawker, 1983: "On the
Calculation of Normal Mode Group Velocity and Attenuation," <i>J. Acoust.
Soc. Am.</i> <b>73</b>, 820-825.<p>

</ul>
</body>
</html>


<hr>

<h3>Current Research</h3>

<ul>

<li>Statistical modeling applied to the El Ni&ntilde;o-Southern
Oscillation (ENSO).

<li>Statistical prediction of tropical Atlantic sea surface temperatures.

<li>Investigation of the physical mechanisms of the stochastic forcing
of IndoPacific sea surface temperatures (with K. Weickmann).

<li>Investigations of air-sea interactions in a 1-dimensional ocean model
(with M. Alexander).

<li>The role of stochastic forcing in a barotropic vorticity model (with
M.  Newman and P. D. Sardeshmukh).

<li>The role of zonal mean wind anomalies on large-scale vorticity
patterns:  "Low frequency wave-mean flow interactions in the troposphere"
(with P. D. Sardeshmukh, to be submitted).
</ul>

<hr>

<h3>Teaching and advising</h3>

<ul>
<li>Member of graduate committee for Mr. Germ&aacute;n Poveda, The
University of Medell&iacute;n, Colombia.  (Prof. Oscar Mesa, advisor).
</ul>

<ul>
<li>Member of Masters' committee for Mr. David Gorodetzky, University
of Colorado, Boulder, Colorado.  (Prof. J. White, advisor).
</ul>
<hr>

<h3>Thesis and Dissertation</h3>

<ul>
<li>"The Effects of Internal Waves on Acoustic Normal Modes,"  PhD 	
dissertation, The University of Texas at Austin,  Fall  1984.

<li>"Latitude Dependence of Soft X-Ray Emission from a Massive Galactic
Halo,"  Master's thesis, Florida Atlantic University, Summer 1977. 
</ul>

<hr>

