<head>
<title>r30 Model</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>r30 Model</h1>
<HR size=4>
One of the simulations conducted as part of the GFDL-University 
Consortium project is a 17 year simulation in which the lower boundary 
conditions repeat the mean seasonal cycle.  Attributes of the model 
simulation are given below.  <p>
<ul>
<li>R30 horizonal resolution (~2.25 latitude x 3.75 longitude)
<li>14 vertical levels
<li>Realistic orography
<li>Seasonally varying insolation
<li>Fixed SST and sea ice, seasonally varying
<li>Predicted clouds
<li>Gravity wave drag
</ul>
<p>
The 14 sigma levels of the model are given below
<pre>
      0.0000 , 0.0300 , 0.0707 , 0.1311 , 0.2102 ,
      0.3036 , 0.4062 , 0.5138 , 0.6226 , 0.7284 ,
      0.8255 , 0.9066 , 0.9640 , 0.9933 , 1.0000 
</pre>
<HR size=4>
<address>
<a href="/gfdl/">The GFDL-University Consortium</a><br>
webmaster@cdc.noaa.gov
</address>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
