<head>
<title>
GFDL-University Consortium R15 Model Experiments
</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>GFDL-University Consortium R15 Model Experiments</h1>
<hr size=4>
<p>
The NOAA/Universities Consortium R30 experiments run to date are listed below.
See specific documentation for each experiment for details.
<p>
<hr size=4>
<p>
<img alt = "o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/blueball.gif">
Idealized experiments
<ul>
<li>Model is a version of the 9-level GFDL climate model
<li>All ocean surface with prescribed SSTs
<li>Insolation fixed at Jan 16 values.
<li>Nine integrations of 4000 days each,
       each with a different sst specification.
       Mid-latitude sst anomalies are superimposed on
       a background sst field resembling boreal winter.
<li>Daily data is available for a subset of model variables.
       4000-day means are available for all other variables.
<li>Dataset size: ~350 MB
<li>contact: pjp@gfdl.gov
</ul>

The following R15 experiments have the following characteristics in  common unless otherwise noted:
<ul>
<li>R15 truncation with 9 sigma-levels in the vertical,
<li>predicted clouds, 
<li>standard model orography ('realistic' continents), 
<li>fixed sst and sea-ice
</ul>

<img alt = "o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/blueball.gif">
100-year Seasonal Experiment
<ul>
<li>monthly climatological prescribed SST and sea-ice
<li>seasonally-varying insolation
<li>Data format: IEEE
<li>Dataset size: ~10.8 GB
<li>See <em>r15_seasonal_100yr_doc</em> for details.
<li>contact: mjn@gfdl.gov
</ul>

<img alt = "o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/blueball.gif">
43-year Seasonal Global Ocean-Global Atmosphere (GOGA) Fixed Cloud Experiment
<ul>
<li>1946-1988 Observed COADS SST anomalies added to monthly 
       climatological prescribed SST and sea-ice
<li>fixed clouds
<li>seasonally-varying insolation
<li>Data format: packed netCDF
<li>Dataset size: ~2.0 GB
<li>See <em>r15_seasonal_gogafxcld_doc</em> for details.
<li>contact: mjn@gfdl.gov
</ul>

<img alt = "o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/blueball.gif">
4 43-year Seasonal Global Ocean-Global Atmosphere (GOGA) Experiments
<ul>
<li>1946-1988 Observed COADS SST anomalies added to monthly 
       climatological prescribed SST and sea-ice
<li>seasonally-varying insolation
<li>Data format: packed netCDF
<li>Dataset size: ~2.0 GB
<li>See <em>r15_seasonal_goga_runs_doc</em> for details.
<li>contact: mjn@gfdl.gov
</ul>

<img alt = "o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/blueball.gif">
Ensemble GOGA Runs (12 each) for years 1968-1973, 1981-1983, 1986-1989
<ul>
<li>same model as for the 4 43-year GOGA runs (see above)
<li>1968-1973, 1981-1983, or 1986-1989 Observed COADS SST anomalies 
added to monthly climatological prescribed SST and sea-ice for each 
of 12 run ensemble.
<li>seasonally-varying insolation
<li>Data format: packed netCDF
<li>Dataset size:
<blockquote>
          1968-1973 runs:  ~4.6 GB <br>
          1981-1983 runs:  ~2.3 GB <br>
          1986-1989 runs:  ~3.1 GB <br>
</blockquote>
<li>See <em>r15_seasonal_goga_12_ensemble_runs</em> for details.
<li>contact: mjn@gfdl.gov
</ul>

<img alt = "o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/blueball.gif">
4 43-year Seasonal Tropical-Pacific Ocean-Global Atmosphere (TOGAPAC)
     Experiment
<ul>
<li>1946-1988 Observed COADS SST anomalies added to monthly 
       climatological prescribed SST in the tropical Pacific between 
       20S and 20N
<li>seasonally-varying insolation
<li>Data format: packed netCDF 
<li>Dataset size: ~2.0 GB
<li>See <em>r15_seasonal_togapac_runs_doc</em> for details.
<li>contact: mjn@gfdl.gov
</ul>
  
<img alt = "o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/blueball.gif">
4 43-year Seasonal Mid_latitude Pacific Ocean-Global Atmosphere (MOGAPAC)
     Experiment
<ul>
<li>1946-1988 Observed COADS SST anomalies added to monthly 
       climatological prescribed SST in the N.H. mid-latitude Pacific between 
       20N-60N
<li>seasonally-varying insolation
<li>Data format: packed netCDF 
<li>Dataset size: ~2.0 GB
<li>See <em>r15_seasonal_mogapac_runs_doc</em> for details.
<li>contact: mjn@gfdl.gov
</ul>
  
<img alt = "o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/blueball.gif">
4 43-year Seasonal Tropical-Pacific Ocean - Global Atmosphere (TOGAQFLUX)
     QFLUX Experiment with predicted global SST outside the TOGA region.
<ul>
<li>1946-1988 Observed COADS SST anomalies added to monthly 
       climatological prescribed SST in the tropical Pacific between 
       20S and 20N 
<li>mixed layer predicted SST outside the TOGA region
<li>seasonally-varying insolation
<li>Data format: packed netCDF 
<li>Dataset size: ~2.0 GB
<li>See <em>r15_seasonal_togaqflux_runs_doc</em> for details.
<li>contact: mjn@gfdl.gov
</ul>

<img alt = "o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/blueball.gif">
10800-day Perpetual January control Experiment
<ul>
<li>fixed January SST and sea-ice
<li>January insolation
<li>fixed soil moisture and snow depth
<li>Data format: packed IEEE
<li>Dataset size: ~1.16 GB
<li>See <em>r15_perpetual_january_control_doc</em> for details
<li>contact: mjn@gfdl.gov
</ul>

<img alt = "o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/blueball.gif">
3000-day Perpetual January "High Mountain" Experiment
<ul>
<li>like control above but with 1.2x topography over western North America
       (Rocky Mtns.)
<li>fixed January SST and sea-ice
<li>January insolation
<li>fixed soil moisture and snow depth
<li>Data format: packed IEEE
<li>Dataset size:
<li>See <em>r15_perpetual_january_highmtn_doc</em> for details
<li>contact: mjn@gfdl.gov
</ul>

<img alt = "o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/blueball.gif">
10800-day Perpetual July control Experiment
<ul>
<li>fixed July SST and sea-ice
<li>July insolation
<li>fixed soil moisture and snow depth
<li>Data format: packed IEEE
<li>Dataset size: ~1.16 GB
<li>See <em>r15_perpetual_july_control_doc</em> for details
<li>contact: mjn@gfdl.gov
</ul>

<img alt = "o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/blueball.gif">
5400-day Perpetual January +1 degree SST Anomaly Experiment
<ul>
<li>fixed January sea-ice and SST with a +1 degree SST anomaly added in
       the North Atlantic
<li>January insolation
<li>fixed soil moisture and snow depth
<li>Data format: packed IEEE
<li>Dataset size: ~632 MB
<li>See <em>r15_perpetual_january_+1degree_doc</em> for details
<li>contact: mjn@gfdl.gov
</ul>

<img alt = "o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/blueball.gif">
5400-day Perpetual January -1 degree SST Anomaly Experiment
<ul>
<li>fixed January sea-ice and SST with a -1 degree SST anomaly added in 
       the North Atlantic
<li>January insolation
<li>fixed soil moisture and snow depth
<li>Data format: packed IEEE
<li>Dataset size: ~632 MB
<li>See <em>r15_perpetual_january_-1degree_doc</em> for details
</ul>

<img alt = "o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/blueball.gif">
6000-day Perpetual January +4 degree SST Anomaly Experiment
<ul>
<li>fixed January sea-ice and SST with a +4 degree SST anomaly added in 
       the North Atlantic
<li>January insolation
<li>fixed soil moisture and snow depth
<li>Data format: packed netCDF
<li>Dataset size: ~658 MB
<li>See <em>r15_perpetual_january_+4degree_doc</em> for details
<li>contact: mjn@gfdl.gov
</ul>

<img alt = "o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/blueball.gif">
6000-day Perpetual January -4 degree SST Anomaly Experiment
<ul>
<li>fixed January sea-ice and SST with a -4 degree SST anomaly added in
       the North Atlantic
<li>January insolation,
<li>fixed soil moisture and snow depth
       Data format: packed netCDF
<li>Dataset size: ~658 MB
<li>See <em>r15_perpetual_january_-4degree_doc</em> for details
<li>contact: mjn@gfdl.gov
</ul>

<img alt = "o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/blueball.gif">
2100-day Perpetual October control Experiment
<ul>
<li>fixed October SST and sea-ice
<li>October insolation
<li>fixed October soil moisture and snow depth
<li>Data format: IEEE (not packed)
<li>Dataset size: ~500MB
<li>See <em>r15_perpetual_october_doc</em> for details
<li>contact: mjn@gfdl.gov
</ul>

<img alt = "o" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/blueball.gif">
2100-day Perpetual October +4 degree K SST Anomaly Experiment
<ul>
<li>fixed October sea-ice and SST with a +4 degree SST anomaly added in
         N.Atlantic
<li>October insolation
<li>fixed October soil moisture and snow depth
<li>Data format: IEEE (not packed)
<li>Dataset size: ~500MB
<li>See <em>r15_perpetual_october_doc</em> for details
<li>contact: mjn@gfdl.gov
</ul>
 
