<title>NCEP/NCAR Reanalysis</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>NCEP/NCAR Reanalysis</h1>
 
<b>Data set identifier:</b> NCEP/NCAR Reanalysis<p>

<b>One-line description:</b>
NCEP/NCAR Reanalysis Data<p> 

<b>Detailed description:</b>
The NCEP/NCAR Reanalysis project is using a state-of-the-art analysis/forecast system
to perform data assimilation using past data from 1958 to the present.<p>
<p>

This document describes NCEP/NCAR Reanalysis data that is currently
available on-line at CDC (this is not all of the data generated by the
Reanalysis).  Additional files will be periodically added.<p>

<b>Important!</b>  If you acquire NCEP/NCAR Reanalysis data products from
CDC, we ask that you acknowledge ("NCAR/NCEP Reanalysis data provided
through the NOAA Climate Diagnostics Center
(http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/)."  CDC in any publications where the data
were used.  We would also appreciate receiving a copy of any papers
published using this data.  Your cooperation will help CDC to justify
keeping the NCEP/NCAR Reanalysis freely available online in the
future.  Thank you!

<p>
<i>Please</i> read the <strong><a href="reanalysis/problems.shtml">problem list</a></strong> before using the data.

<hr>

<h2>The NCEP/NCAR Reanalysis descriptions here are subdivided into
separate data sets</h2>

<strong>
These are currently:
<ul>
<li><a href="#pressure">Pressure Level Data</a>
<li><a href="#surface2.5">Surface Data</a>
<li><a href="#surface_gauss">Surface Flux Data</a>
<li><a href="#other_gauss">Other Flux Data</a>
<li><a href="#tropopause">Tropopause</a>
<li><a href="#spectral">T62 Spectral Coefficients</a>
</ul>
</strong>
Jump to:  <a href="#other_info">Other General Information</a>

<p>

<hr>

<h2><a name="pressure">Pressure Level Data</a></h2>


<b>Archive parameters:</b> File names are composed of variable
abbreviations and year:

<pre>
(variable).(year).nc
								Least
Variables on pressure levels:		File	Units		Sig. Digit
----------------------------		----	-----		----------
  Air temperature 			air	degK		0.1 
  Geopotential height 			hgt	m		1. 
  Relative humidity 			rhum	%		1.
  Specific humidity 			shum	kg/kg		0.00001
  Omega (vertical velocity)		omega	Pascal/s	0.001
  U-wind 				uwnd	m/s		0.1
  V-wind 				vwnd	m/s		0.1

</pre>

<b>Note:</b><p>
These variables are instantaneous values at the reference time.<p>

<b>Spatial coverage:</b>
<ul>
<li>2.5-degree latitude x 2.5-degree 
longitude global grid with 144x73 points.
<li>90N-90S, 0E-357.5E
</ul>


<b>Temporal coverage:</b>
<ul>
<li>1/1/1979 - 12/31/1995 with output every 6 hours
</ul>


<b>Levels:</b> 
<ul> 
<li>17 pressure levels (hPa): 1000, 925, 850, 700, 600, 500, 400, 300,
250, 200, 150, 100, 70, 50, 30, 20, 10
<li>some variables not defined at all levels
</ul> 

<b>Missing data:</b>
<ul>
<li>None
</ul>


<b>Search keywords:</b><br>
geopotential, height, humidity, omega, potential, pressure, relative,
specific, temperature, velocity, vertical, wind
<p>

<b>Data set format and size:</b>
<ul>
<li>All data are stored in netCDF files
<li>The data are divided by variable and year into separate files
<li>There are 98 files currently
<li>Sizes range from 245 Mbytes to 521 Mbytes per variable per year
<li>Current total of 40.3 Gbytes
</ul>

<b>Availability and usage restrictions:</b>
<ul>
<li>Samples available by anonymous FTP from ftp.cdc.noaa.gov in 
/Datasets/nmc.reanalysis/pressure_samples
<li><b>Complete data files are only available outside of CDC by request on
8mm tapes due to large file sizes.</b> To order, contact <a href =
"http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc/email_form.shtml">cdcdata@cdc.noaa.gov</a> or
use the 
<a href = "http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cgi-bin/OrderData.pl?directory=pressure">
on-line order form.</a>
There is no service charge, but we will require you to send us
enough data-quality tapes to hold your request.
<li>No usage restrictions
</ul>

<hr>

<h2><a name="surface2.5">Surface Data</a></h2>

<b>Archive parameters:</b> File names are composed of variable
abbreviations, level, and year:

<pre>
(variable).(level).(year).nc
									Least
Variables on or near the surface:	File		Units		Sig. Digit
----------------------------		----		-----		----------
  Air Temperature			air.sig995	degK		 0.1
  Surface lifted index			lftx.sfc	degK		 0.1
  Best (4-layer) lifted index		lftx4.sfc	degK		 0.1
  Omega	(vertical velocity)		omega.sig995	Pascal/s	 0.001
  Potential temperature			pottmp.sig995	degK		 0.1
  Precipitable water                    pr_wtr.eatm     kg/m^2           0.1
  Pressure				pres.sfc	Pascals		10.
  Relative humidity			rhum.sig995	%		 1.
  Sea level pressure			slp		Pascals		10.
  U-wind				uwnd.sig995	m/s		 0.1
  V-wind				vwnd.sig995	m/s		 0.1

  Geopotential hgt (time invariant) *	hgt.sfc		m		 1.

* = no year in file name
</pre>

<b>Note:</b><p>
These variables are instantaneous values at the reference time.<p>

<b>Spatial coverage:</b>
<ul>
<li>2.5-degree latitude x 2.5-degree longitude global grid with 144x73 points
<li>90N-90S, 0E-357.5E
</ul>

<b>Temporal coverage:</b>
<ul>
<li>1/1/1979 - 12/31/1995 with output every 6 hours
</ul>

<b>Levels:</b> 
<ul> 
<li>Surface or near the surface (.995 sigma level)
<li><p>Also, precipitable water is included here, because it is a 3-D file on a
2.5 degree grid, but it is not a surface value, but rather for the entire
atmospheric column<p>
</ul> 

<b>Missing data:</b>
<ul>
<li>None
</ul>

<b>Search keywords:</b><br>
geopotential, height, humidity, index, lifted, omega, potential,
pressure, relative, sea, temperature, velocity, vertical, wind
<p>

<b>Data set format and size:</b>
<ul>
<li>All data are stored in netCDF files
<li>The data are divided by variable and year into separate files
<li>There are 141 files currently
<li>Files are 30 Mbytes per variable per year
<li>Current total of 4.2 Gbytes
</ul>

<b>Availability and usage restrictions:</b>
<ul>
<li>Data files available by anonymous FTP from ftp.cdc.noaa.gov in /Datasets/nmc.reanalysis/surface or
use the 
<a href = "http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cgi-bin/OrderData.pl?directory=surface">
on-line order form.</a>
<li>No restrictions
</ul>

<hr>

<h2><a name="surface_gauss">Surface Flux Data</a></h2>

<b>Archive parameters:</b> File names are composed of variable
abbreviations, level, and year:

<pre>
(variable).(level).gauss.(year).nc
									Least
Variables on or near the surface:	File		Units		Sig. Digit
----------------------------		----		-----		----------
  Air Temperature			air.sfc		degK		0.1
  Air Temperature at 2 meters		air.2m		degK		0.1
  Cloud forcing net longwave flux	cfnlf.sfc	W/m^2		1.
  Cloud forcing net solar flux		cfnsf.sfc	W/m^2		1.
  Convective precipitation rate		cprat.sfc	Kg/m^2/s	0.000001
  Clear sky downward longwave flux	csdlf.sfc	W/m^2		1.
  Clear sky downward solar flux		csdsf.sfc	W/m^2		1.
  Downward longwave radiation flux	dlwrf.sfc	W/m^2		1.
  Downward solar radiation flux		dswrf.sfc	W/m^2		1.
  Ground heat flux			gflux.sfc	W/m^2		1.
  Ice concentration			icec.sfc	(0 or 1)	1.
  Latent heat net flux			lhtfl.sfc	W/m^2		1.
  Near IR beam downward solar flux	nbdsf.sfc	W/m^2		1.
  Near IR diffuse downward solar flux	nddsf.sfc	W/m^2		1.
  Potential evaporation rate		pevpr.sfc	W/m^2		1.
  Precipitation rate			prate.sfc	Kg/m^2/s	0.000001
  Pressure				pres.sfc	Pascals	       10.
  Water runoff				runof.sfc	Kg/m^2		0.1
  Surface roughness  			sfcr.sfc	m		0.00001
  Specific humidity at 2 meters		shum.2m		kg/kg		0.0001
  Sensible heat net flux		shtfl.sfc	W/m^2		1.
  Volumetric soil moisture (0-10cm)	soilw.0-10cm	fraction	0.001
  Volumetric soil moisture (10-200cm)	soilw.10-200cm	fraction	0.001
  Maximum temperature at 2m layer	tmax.2m		degK		0.1
  Minimum temperature at 2m layer	tmin.2m		degK		0.1
  Temperature of 0-10cm layer		tmp.0-10cm	degK		0.1
  Temperature of 10-200cm layer		tmp.10-200cm	degK		0.1
  Temperature at 300cm			tmp.300cm	degK		0.1
  Zonal component of momentum flux	uflx.sfc	N/m^2		0.001
  Zonal gravity wave stress		ugwd.sfc	N/m^2		0.001
  Upward longwave radiation flux	ulwrf.sfc	W/m^2		1.
  Upward solar radiation flux		uswrf.sfc	W/m^2		1.
  U-wind at 10 m			uwnd.10m	m/s		0.1
  Visible beam downward solar flux	vbdsf.sfc	W/m^2		1.
  Visible diffuse downward solar flux	vddsf.sfc	W/m^2		1.
  Meridional component of momentum flux	vflx.sfc	N/m^2		0.001
  Meridional gravity wave stress	vgwd.sfc	N/m^2		0.001
  V-wind at 10 m			vwnd.10m	m/s		0.1
  Water equiv. of accum. snow depth	weasd.sfc	kg/m^2		1.
  Net longwave radiation 		nlwrs.sfc	W/m^2		1.
  Net shortwave radiation		nswrs.sfc	W/m^2		1.
  Land-sea mask (time invariant) *	land.sfc	(0 or 1)	1.

* = no year in file name

</pre>

<b>Note:</b><p>
The following variables are instantaneous values at the reference time:
air.sfc, air.2m, icec.sfc, pres.sfc, runof.sfc, sfcr.sfc, shum.2m, soilw.0-10cm,
soilw.10-200cm, tmax.2m, tmin.2m, tmp.0-10cm, tmp.10-200cm, tmp.300cm, uwnd.10m,
vwnd.10m, weasd.sfc, land.sfc
<p>
The following variables are six hour averages for the period of the reference
time plus six hours:
cfnlf.sfc, sfnsf.sfc, cprat.sfc, csdlf.sfc, csdsf.sfc, dlwrf.sfc, dswrf.sfc,
gflux.sfc, lhtfl.sfc, nbdsf.sfc, nddsf.sfc, prate.sfc, shtfl.sfc, uflx.sfc,
ugwd.sfc, ulwrf.sfc, uswrf.sfc, vbdsf.sfc, vddsf.sfc, vflx.sfc, vgwd.sfc, 
nlwrs.sfc, nswrs.sfc
<p>

<b>Spatial coverage:</b>
<ul>
<li>T62 Gaussian grid with 192x94 points
<li>88.542N-88.542S, 0E-358.125E
</ul>

<b>Temporal coverage:</b>
<ul>
<li>1/1/1979 - 12/31/1995 with output every 6 hours
</ul>

<b>Levels:</b> 
<ul> 
<li>Surface or near the surface
</ul> 

<b>Missing data:</b>
<ul>
<li>None
</ul>

<b>Search keywords:</b><br>
beam, clear, cloud, concentration, convective, depth, diffuse,
downward, evaporation, flux, gravity, ground, heat, humidity, ice, IR,
land-sea, latent, longwave, mask, maximum, meridional, minimum,
moisture, momentum, near, net, potential, precipitation, pressure,
radiation, roughness, runoff, sensible, sky, soil, snow, solar,
specific, stress, upward, visible, volumetric, water, wave, wind,
zonal
<p>

<b>Data set format and size:</b>
<ul>
<li>All data are stored in netCDF files
<li>The data are divided by variable and year into separate files
<li>There are 594 files currently
<li>Files are 52 Mbytes per variable per year
<li>Current total of 30.5 Gbytes
</ul>

<b>Availability and usage restrictions:</b>
<ul>
<li>Data files available by anonymous FTP from ftp.cdc.noaa.gov in /Datasets/nmc.reanalysis/surface_gauss
 or
use the 
<a href = "http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cgi-bin/OrderData.pl?directory=surface_gauss">
on-line order form.</a>
<li>No restrictions
</ul>
<hr>
<h2><a name="other_gauss">Other Flux Data</a></h2>

<b>Archive parameters:</b> File names are composed of variable abbreviations,
level, and year:

<pre>
(variable).(level).gauss.(year).nc
									Least
Variables not for the surface:		File		Units		Sig. Digit
----------------------------		----		-----		----------
  Clear sky upward longwave flux        csulf.ntat	W/m^2            1.
  Clear sky upward solar flux           csusf.ntat      W/m^2            1.
  Downward solar radiation flux         dswrf.ntat      W/m^2            1.
  Pressure at high cloud bottom         pres.hcb        Pascals         10.
  Pressure at high cloud top            pres.hct        Pascals         10.
  Pressure at low cloud bottom          pres.lcb        Pascals         10.
  Pressure at low cloud top             pres.lct        Pascals         10.
  Pressure at middle cloud bottom       pres.mcb        Pascals         10.
  Pressure at middle cloud top          pres.mct        Pascals         10.
  Total cloud cover                     tcdc.eatm       %                1.
  Upward longwave radiation flux        ulwrf.ntat      W/m^2            1.
  Upward solar radiation flux           uswrf.ntat      W/m^2            1.

</pre>

<b>Spatial coverage:</b>
<ul>
<li>T62 Gaussian grid with 192x94 points
<li>88.542N-88.542S, 0E-358.125E
</ul>
 
<b>Temporal coverage:</b>
<ul>
<li>1/1/1979-12/31/1995 with output every 6 hours.
</ul>

<b>Levels:</b>
<ul>
<li>ntat:  Nominal top of atmosphere
<li>eatm:  Entire atmosphere
<li>hcb:   High cloud bottom
<li>hct:   High cloud top
<li>lcb:   Low cloud bottom
<li>lct:   Low cloud top
<li>mcb:   Middle cloud bottom
<li>mct:   Middle cloud top
</ul>

<b>Missing data:</b>
<ul>
<li>None
</ul>

<b>Search keywords:</b><br>
clear, cloud, downward, flux, longwave, pressure, radiation, solar, upward
<p>

<b>Data set format and size:</b>
<ul>
<li>All data are stored in netCDF files
<li>The data are divided by variable and year into separate files
<li>There are 12 files currently
<li>Files 52 Mbytes per variable per year
<li>Current total of 632 Mbytes
</ul>
<b>Availability and usage restrictions:</b>
<ul>
<li>Data files available by anonymous FTP from ftp.cdc.noaa.gov in /Datasets/nmc.reanalysis/other_gauss or
use the 
<a href = "http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cgi-bin/OrderData.pl?directory=other_gauss">
on-line order form.</a>
<li>No restrictions
</ul>

<hr>
<h2><a name="tropopause">Tropopause Level Data</a></h2>


<b>Archive parameters:</b> File names are composed of variable
abbreviations and year:

<pre>
(variable).tropp.(year).nc
								Least
Variables at the tropopause :		File	Units		Sig. Digit
----------------------------		----	-----		----------
  Air temperature 			air	degK		0.01 
  Pressure				pres	Pascals		1.0

</pre>

<b>Note:</b><p>
These variables are instantaneous values at the reference time.<p>

<b>Spatial coverage:</b>
<ul>
<li>2.5-degree latitude x 2.5-degree 
longitude global grid with 144x73 points.
<li>90N-90S, 0E-357.5E
</ul>


<b>Temporal coverage:</b>
<ul>
<li>1/1/1979 - 12/31/1995 with output every 6 hours
</ul>


<b>Levels:</b> 
<ul> 
<li>Tropopause
</ul> 

<b>Missing data:</b>
<ul>
<li>None
</ul>


<b>Search keywords:</b><br>
air temperature, pressure
<p>

<b>Data set format and size:</b>
<ul>
<li>All data are stored in netCDF files
<li>The data are divided by variable and year into separate files
<li>There are 28 files currently
<li>Each file is about 31 megabytes.
<li>Current total of 841 Mbytes
</ul>

<b>Availability and usage restrictions:</b>
<ul>
<li>Data files available by anonymous FTP from ftp.cdc.noaa.gov in /Datasets/nmc.reanalysis/tropopause or
use the
<a href = "http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cgi-bin/OrderData.pl?directory=tropopause">
on-line order form.</a>
<li>No restrictions
</ul>

<hr>

<h2><a name="spectral">T62 Spectral Coefficients</a></h2>


<b>Archive parameters:</b> File names are composed of variable
abbreviations and year:

<pre>
(variable).spec.(year).nc
								Least
Variables as spectral coeffs.:		File	Units		Sig. Digit
----------------------------		----	-----		----------
  Divergence 				div	1./s		0.1 
  Orography 				orog	m		n/a
  Natural Log of Pressure		pres	nlog(centibars) 1.0
  Specific Humidity			shum	kg/kg		0.0001
  Virtual Air Temperature		vair	degK		1.0
  Vorticity				vort	1./s		0.1

</pre>

<b>Note:</b><p>
These variables are instantaneous values at the reference time.<p>

<b>Spatial coverage:</b>
<ul>
<li>T62 Spectral Coefficients
</ul>


<b>Temporal coverage:</b>
<ul>
<li>1/1/1979 - 12/31/1995 with output every 6 hours
</ul>


<b>Levels:</b> 
<ul> 
<li>28 Sigma levels: 0.995, 0.9821, 0.9644, 0.9425, 0.9159, 0.8838, 0.8458, 
     0.8014, 0.7508, 0.6943, 0.6329, 0.5681, 0.5017, 0.4357, 0.372, 
     0.3125, 0.2582, 0.2101, 0.1682, 0.1326, 0.1028, 0.0782, 0.058, 
     0.0418, 0.0288, 0.0183, 0.0101, 0.0027
<li>Some variables not defined at all levels.
</ul> 

<b>Missing data:</b>
<ul>
<li>None
</ul>


<b>Search keywords:</b><br>
Divergence, orography, natural log of pressure, specific humidity, virtual
air temperature, vorticity
<p>

<b>Data set format and size:</b>
<ul>
<li>All data are stored in netCDF files
<li>The data are divided by variable and year into separate files
<li>There are 71 files currently
<li>Sizes range from 17 Kbytes to 331 Mbytes per variable per year
<li>Current total of 18.2 Gbytes
</ul>

<b>Availability and usage restrictions:</b>
<ul>
<li>Data files available by anonymous FTP from ftp.cdc.noaa.gov in /Datasets/nmc.reanalysis/spectral or
use the
<a href = "http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cgi-bin/OrderData.pl?directory=spectral">
on-line order form.</a>
<li>No usage restrictions
</ul>

<hr>

