<title>NMC Reanalysis - netCDF file descriptions and sizes</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>NMC Reanalysis - netCDF file descriptions and sizes</h1>

This document describes the proposed file names for the various
datasets within the NMC Reanalysis.  The estimated sizes for these
datasets are also included, with totals for possible implementation
scenarios.  Not all of these datasets or all the variables within them
will necessarily be converted to netCDF or put online.<p>

For each data file, the first part of the file will be identical to
the variable name inside the file.  In general, each file will contain
one year of data ("YY" in the file name) for one variable.  For
monthly means and covariances, the files generally will contain all
the years currently available.  The current status of which of these
files are created and where they are stored is not described here.<p>

<h2>Reanalysis Datasets:</h2>

<ul>
<pre>
<li><A HREF="datasets/pressure.html">Pressure - 17 levels, 6-hr, 2.5 deg (144x73)</A>
522 MB x 4 vars + 368 MB x 2 vars + 246 MB	=  3.1 GB
(excludes absolute vorticity)

<li><A HREF="datasets/surface2.5.html">Surface data - 6-hr, 2.5 deg (144x73)</A>
31 MB x 10 vars					=  0.3 GB


<li><A HREF="datasets/surface_gauss.html">Surface/flux - 6-hr, gaussian (192x94)</A> 
52 MB x 44 vars 				=  2.3 GB


<li><A HREF="datasets/one_level_gauss.html">Non-surface - 1 level, 6-hr, gaussian (192x94)</A>
53 MB x 29 vars					=  1.5 GB


<li><A HREF="datasets/one_level2.5.html">Non-surface - 1 level, 6-hr, 2.5 deg (144x73)</A>
31 MB x 18 vars					=  0.6 GB


<li><A HREF="datasets/sigma_gauss.html">Sigma - 28 levels, 6-hr, gaussian (192x94)</A>
1478 MB x 6 vars + 6 related surface vars	=  9.2 GB


<li><A HREF="datasets/sigma_spectral.html">Sigma - 28 levels, 6-hr, spectral coeffs</A>
335 MB x 4 vars	+ 2 related surface vars	=  1.3 GB


<li><A HREF="datasets/sigma_guess.html">Sigma guess - 28 levels, 6-hr, spectral coeffs</A>
335 MB x 4 vars	+ 1 related surface var 	=  1.3 GB


<li><A HREF="datasets/theta.html">Theta - 11 levels, 6-hr, 2.5 deg
(144x73)</A> 338 MB x 11 vars + 1 related surface var = 3.7 GB


<li><A HREF="datasets/heating.html">Heating - 28 sigma levels, 6-hr, gaussian (192x94)</A>
1478 MB x 11 vars				= 16.3 GB


<li>Monthly means & co-variances
<ul>
<li><A HREF="datasets/pressure_mm.html">pressure</A>:  11 MB x 56 vars		=  0.6 GB/yr
<li><A HREF="datasets/surface2.5_mm.html">surface (2.5 deg)</A>:  <1 MB x 4 vars	= <0.1 GB/yr
<li><A HREF="datasets/surface_gauss_mm.html">surface (gaussian)</A>:  1 MB x 124 vars	=  0.1 GB/yr
<li><A HREF="datasets/one_level2.5_mm.html">1-level (2.5 deg)</A>:  <1 MB x 2 vars	= <0.1 GB/yr
<li><A HREF="datasets/one_level_gauss_mm.html">1-level (gaussian)</A>:  1 MB x 56 vars	=  0.1 GB/yr 
<li><A HREF="datasets/theta_mm.html">theta</A>:	7 MB x 26 vars			=  0.2 GB/yr
<li><A HREF="datasets/heating_mm.html">heating</A>:  31 MB x 6 vars		=  0.2 GB/yr
</ul>
  total of monthly means & co-variances		= ~1.3  GB
</ul>
================================================================
Total size per year				= 41.0 GB
    Totals for 1982-94 (13 years)   =  530 GB
    Totals for 1958-94 (37 years)   = 1520 GB
				     ========

ALTERNATIVES:
------------
Total size per year without Sigma gaussian 	= 31.8 GB
    Totals for 1982-94 (13 years)   =  410 GB
    Totals for 1958-94 (37 years)   = 1180 GB
				     ========

Total size per year without Sigma gaussian 	
	& theta level data			= 28.1 GB
    Totals for 1982-94 (13 years)   =  370 GB
    Totals for 1958-94 (37 years)   = 1040 GB
				     ========
</pre>

</body>
