<TITLE>CDC Map Room Weather Products</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<center>
<a href="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov">
<img alt="Climate Diagnostics Center" src="http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/cdc_images/banner.gif"></a>
</center>
<B>
<P>
<CENTER><H1><A name="top">CDC Map Room Weather Products</a></H1></CENTER>

<HR SIZE=3>
<p>
The CDC Map Room Weather Page is designed to provide
a quick and easy reference point for current forecast
products available from the National Centers for Environmental 
Prediction (NCEP).   Currently, the products available
on this page are being developed with the use of
data being provided through NCEP.  The products 
are primarily being produced with the use of
<A HREF="http://grads.iges.org/grads/"> GrADS</A> and 
<A HREF="http://www.rsinc.com/idl/"> IDL</A>.

<HR SIZE=3>
<B><img alt="warn" src="/~map/caution.tiny.gif">It is possible that we may be
dropping from the Unidata IDD network in the coming days.  This will be causing
some changes in some of the products that we provide.  This will be most
noticeable in the 'Current Weather Products' section.  The biggest change
will be to plots containing surface data such as analysis plots.  If we do
in fact drop the data feed, we will do our best to provide replacement links
for the products that are affected.  We do get much of our data from NCEP, so
model runs such as the MRF, ETA, and AVN will not change.  Also, our coverage
of the NCEP Ensemble Data Forecasts will continue as always.</B>
<HR SIZE=3>
